Commentary: Anderson on the money! Short of a length, lands on off and shapes back in. There is quite a bit of bounce on that one and Warner is taken by surprise. He manages to get some glove on it. Warner then goes down the track and taps the exact spot where the ball landed.
Fuller and angling across off. Warner plants his front foot forward and leaves it.
On a length, just outside off. Left alone again.
Anderson is getting some nice shape and carry here. Angling across off and left alone. Buttler collects it with the fingers pointing upwards.
Gets it to come back in! Anderson lands it on off and shapes it back in. Warner works it past square leg and gets a single. First runs of the Test.

Tap and run! Full and on off. Tapped to short cover and they take off for a single. Warner has to dive in the end as the fielder throws the ball at his end. We have to wait for the Broad vs Warner battle. Assuming that the pacer will bowl the next over.
Comes 'round the wicket and bowls a shorter one, outside off. Harris doesn't chase it.
Fuller, lands on off and coming back in. Harris looks to block it from the crease but gets hit on the pads.
Nice and full, on off. Harris is equally solid in his defence.
Length ball, 130 kmph, outside off. Harris covers the stumps and lets Buttler collect this one.
A touch shorter, outside off. It angles back in and Harris blocks it out.
A solid defence off the crease by Harris to end the over. A decent start for Broad too.
That is good shape! Anderson serves a length ball, landing on middle and shaping away. Warner leaves it on length and the ball sails over the stumps.
Similar length but wide enough for Warner to leave it with ease.
Nice areas. Tempting Warner to drive with a length ball, just outside off. But the southpaw leaves it.
A bit of shape in this time. Fuller, lands on middle and comes back in. Warner taps it to the leg side.
A bit too wide again and Warner has no qualms in leaving this one.
Short of a length, on the sixth-stump line. Left alone again by Warner.
Quick single! Length ball, outside off. Harris taps it towards point and takes off. Haseeb Hameed charges in and fires a throw at the bowler's end but misses. Here we go. Warner vs Broad.
Nice and full. Making Warner play as the left-hander blocks it from the crease.
This jags back in with the angle after landing on off. Warner looks to block but gets hit on the pads.
FOUR! Top shot by Warner! A bit overpitched, outside off. Warner gets low and drives it past covers for a boundary. Broad would not mind that though.
Well bowled! On a length, in the corridor of uncertainty. A bit of away shape too. Warner covers the stumps and leaves it.
Fuller and around off. Warner gets the outside edge while looking to block. It goes past the diving gully fielder for one.
On a length, on the pads. Warner taps it to the leg side.
A bit fuller, on middle. Warner stays in the crease and blocks it out. Warne in the commentary box reckons that Anderson might bowl straighter now.
Full, on middle. Warner stays solid in his defence.
Anderson bowls it full and wide outside off. Left alone.
A bit closer to the off pole but still wide enough for Warner to leave it.
Length and on the pads. Warner looks to block but gets rapped on the pads.
Fuller, around off. Harris pushes it to short cover.
Short and way, way outside off. Harris does not chase it.
Broad bowls it fuller, on off. Harris puts in half a stride to block it.
Caught in two minds! Broad bowls it on a length, just outside off. Harris decides to leave it a bit too late. The ball takes the toe end of the bat and rolls to the slip cordon.
A bit shorter, around off. Harris gets the outside edge towards gully.
Nice and full, outside off. Harris reaches out but then leaves it alone.
On a length, around off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Another good shot by Warner! A touch fuller and wider. Warner shifts his weight forward and nicely plays it past covers for a boundary.
Anderson bowls it full and on middle. Giving Warner no room as he blocks it out.
FOUR LEG BYES! Wrong line again. Length and on the pads. Warner gets some pad on it and the ball runs to the fine leg fence.

Back to bowling on off is Anderson and back to blocking is Warner. The approach by the southpaw seems to be punishing the bad deliveries and respecting the good ones. A good approach in the first session of any Test match.
Short of a length, around off. Blocked away.
Play and a miss! Short and wide outside off. Harris decides to cash in and goes for the mighty cut. But he gets no bat on it.
On a length, around off. Harris blocks it from the crease.
Well bowled! Full and on middle. The angle has Harris looking to flick it away but the ball holds its line. It takes the leading edge and goes towards cover.
This time Harris works it past mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Short of a length, around off. Blocked out.

Peach of a delivery! They need to bowl more of those with the overcast conditions there to assist them. Length ball, around off. It lands and holds its line. Harris looks to block it but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Full and straight. Blocked towards mid on.
FOUR! Down the ground! Anderson goes 'round the wickets and serves a full one, on middle. Warner punches it down the ground. Anderson sticks his left hand out but cannot stop it. Boundary.

That is close! This is well bowled by Anderson. Length ball, jagging back with the angle. Warner is stuck in the crease while looking to block and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal but not given. Anderson signals to Root that it might have been sliding down leg. The review is not taken.
On a length, around off. Tapped to point.
Length, outside off. Left alone.
Well bowled. Full and on middle. Warner gets hit on the pads again while looking to block.
FOUR! Broad digs it in short, around chest height. Marcus Harris takes it on and pulls it into the square leg fence for a boundary.
A length ball, on top of middle. Harris defends it out off the back foot.
A touch fuller this time, on off. Blocked out.
Fuller delivery, angled into off stump. Harris drives it on the up straight towards short cover.
Length again, around middle and defended on the off side by Harris.
Around off, Harris just opens the face of the bat and plays it with soft hands through cover-point for a single.
Pitched up, around middle and leg. Harris defends it towards mid on.
Short of a length, outside off. Harris leaves this one alone.
Beaten! On a good length, angled into off. The ball straightens after pitching and just goes past the outside edge of Harris' willow.
A length ball, on middle. Harris presses forward to defend.
On middle, Harris stays solid in defense.
Length again, sliding into leg stump this time. Harris tucks it through square leg and collects a couple of runs.
Stokes starts off with a very full ball, on middle. Warner jams it out to cover-point.
A length ball, around off and angling across the left-hander. Warner watches it all the way through and leaves it alone.
On the pads, tucked away to deep backward square leg. Warner pushes hard for two but decides against it in the end.
Good carry! A length ball, around off and Harris shoulders arms.
Length again, outside off and angling across. Left alone.
Slightly pitched up, in that channel around off. Harris makes an assured leave.
Wood starts from 'round the wicket and hurls across a length ball, on off. Warner defends it out with ease.
On off and angling in, Warner defends it with soft hands towards short cover.
Length again, at 145 kph. This one nips in sharply after pitching on off stump. Warner manages to keep it out.
Runs straightaway! Mark Wood starts off with a very full ball, on middle. David Warner punches it down the ground for a couple.
FOUR! Full and wide, Warner creams this one through cover-point and picks up a boundary.
Back of a length, over middle and at 146 kph. Warner hops to tap it back onto the deck.
A length ball, on off. Harris defends it off the front foot.
A bumper this time, over the leg stump. Marcus Harris ducks under it.
Back of a length, on off and angling across. Harris goes on the back foot to block it out.
Slightly fuller, on off and drawing the batter forward. Harris drives it straight to short cover.
Shorter in length, on off. Harris stays solid in defense.
On middle and leg, this one skids through and Harris does well to block it out. Maiden over from Ben Stokes.
Good-length ball, outside off and angled in. Warner lets it through to the keeper.
Beaten! Another length ball at 146 kph, around the off pole and angled into the left-hander. This one straightens a bit after pitching and whizzes past the outside edge.
On off and this is punched towards the covers.
Right on the money from Wood! On top of off and Warner taps it towards the gully region.
Back of a length, around off. Warner looks to drop and run but decides against it.
This time Wood attacks the pads with a slightly fuller one. Warner looks to work it away on the leg side but gets a leading edge on the off side. End of another maiden over.
Pitched up, around the fifth-stump line. Harris makes a watchful leave.
NO BALL! Short and a bit wide. Marcus Harris cuts it off the back foot but can't get it through point. A no ball is called as Ben Stokes oversteps.
On the pads, this is flicked through square leg for one.
Around off and this is driven nicely. The man at extra cover though makes a good stop.
WIDE! Stokes looks for the quick bumper but this one goes well above Warner's head. A wide is signalled.

Jaffa! On a length, on off and seems to be angling across the left-hander. The ball just holds its line and David Warner gets completely caught on the crease. The ball just goes past his outside edge.
Length again, outside off and Warner makes an easy leave.

NO BALL! Slight mix-up but Warner survives. This is outside off and Warner just runs it to backward point. He looks for a quick single and Harris does well to send him back. Stokes has overstepped once again and a no ball is called.
Pitched up, around off and left alone by Warner.
Good-length ball, outside off. Harris shoulders arms.
Wood hits the length hard and bowls this one over off stump. Harris defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller one, around 147 kph. Harris looks to drive on the off side but the ball comes off the inner half of the bat and goes towards mid on.
On the pads and flicked away straight to square leg.
Wood attacks the pads yet again and Harris gets cramped for room. The ball goes off the pads and rolls onto the leg side.
Wood comes from over the wicket now. A length ball around 150 kph, on top of off and this is left alone by Harris. Another maiden for Mark Wood and he is turning up the heat for sure.
Full and wide, Warner mistimes the cover drive towards mid off.

FOUR! Chance! Back of a length, around off. David Warner is pushed back as he looks to block it out but gets squared up. The ball goes off the outside edge and flies past Zak Crawley at second slip and runs away into the fence.
Close! A length ball, around off. Warner makes the leave and the ball goes agonizingly over the off stump.
FOUR! Perfectly timed from David Warner. This is pitched up, around off and Warner gets it through extra cover for a boundary.
On off and pushed towards mid off.
A length ball, angled into middle and leg. Warner defends it out.
Wood hits the deck hard at 148 kph and bowls it on off. Harris plays it off the back foot towards point.
This is pitched further up, at almost 150 kph. Harris drives it off the inner half of the bat towards mid on.
Slight width on offer this time. Marcus Harris hops back and slaps it straight to cover-point.
A quick bumper at 148.5 kph and over middle stump. Harris ducks under it.
On a good length, around off. Harris manages to get it past cover for a quick single.
Wood goes full, on middle stump and delivers this one at 152 kph. Warner hangs back and just eases it through the cover region for a single.
A gentle half-volley on the off stump. Warner punches it but straight to silly mid on.
Fuller delivery, angled into middle and leg. Warner keeps it out on the off side.
A length ball, in that channel around off. David Warner shoulders arms.
On top of middle stump, Warner defends it back towards the bowler.
A well-directed short ball this time from Stokes. This one pitches outside off and is angled in. David Warner sways his head away from it.
Back of a length, around middle. Warner keeps it out off the back foot. End of a maiden over from Ben Stokes.
On a length, on off. Tapped past covers for one.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Full and on middle. Blocked out by Warner.
Length and down the leg side. Buttler dives to his right to stop the ball.
Length and just outside off. But Warner leaves it with ease.

OUT! TAKEN! Straight to the man! Finally, Warner departs and it is none other than Broad to take the first wicket. It took a lot longer than they would have liked but this wicket provides them with an opportunity to put some pressure on the Aussies. Broad bowls a length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. Warner pushes at it but the ball tails away late and takes the outside edge. The ball goes to second slip and Zak Crawley pouches it.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
On a length, around off. Harris blocks it from the crease.

FIVE WIDES! What in the world was that bounce? Ben Stokes digs in a short ball, around middle the stump. The ball bounces like a tennis ball and just bounces way, way over Harris' head. Jos Buttler has no chance of getting a glove on it. The ball races away into the boundary and everyone across the ground is having a laugh about it, well everyone except Stokes.
Full and down the leg side. Harris misses the flick.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Stokes serves a length ball, wide outside off. Harris leaves it alone.
On a length, on off. Blocked out by Harris.
On a length, outside off. A typical Marnus Labuschagne leave is the result.
On a length, on middle. Labuschagne works it to square leg for one.
Fuller and on off. Blocked out nicely off the front foot.
FOUR! Top, top shot by Marnus Labuschagne! A touch fuller, just outside off. He plants his foot forward and drives it nicely down the ground. The man at short extra cover dives but cannot get there.
Length ball, around off. Left alone with ease.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne taps it to the leg side.
Wood bowls it full, on off. Harris blocks it out towards cover.
Back of a length, 141 kph, on off. Harris stays in the crease and blocks it with ease.
Length, on off. Harris taps it towards mid on. They think of a single for a second but decide against it.
FOUR! Full now, on off. Harris drives it past the diving mid on fielder and gets a boundary.
A typical pacer's response. Short and down the leg side. It goes way over Harris and Buttler does well to leap and stick his right hand out to gather it. Wide called.
More runs. Back of a length, outside off. Harris looks to block but gets the outside edge past backward point for a couple.
Well bowled! On a length, just outside off. Harris wants to block it so hangs his bat out. But the ball shapes away just enough to beat the outside edge.
On a length, lands just outside off and comes back in. Blocked out by Marnus.
FOUR! Frustrating for Broad! Full and on off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to work it straighter but gets the leading edge. The ball goes past the diving third slip for a boundary.
FOUR! Lucky again! Length and on the pads. This is flicked down the leg side by Marnus Labuschagne. Jos Buttler throws himself to his left but cannot get there.

Appeal for LBW! Length and on off. It comes back in after landing and Marnus Labuschagne is struck on the pads while looking to block. There is a big appeal by Broad but the umpire is not interested. Root has a word with Broad and decides not to review. Could be too high. Oh, there is a big inside edge on that.
Fullish ball, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it straight to short mid-wicket.
A length ball, outside off and left alone.
Length, on the pads. Clipped away past square leg for one.

Thank you Marnus Labuschagne! That woke me up! The moment he left this ball outside off, Marnus Labuschagne let off a huge 'wooooo'. That certainly woke me up. That was well bowled though. Tempting the batter to play at it. Marnus was impressed with that clearly.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Short of a length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it.
Yet another solid defence off the crease by Marnus.
A touch fuller, on off. But the result is the same and Marnus Labuschagne is solid in his defence.
Fuller, on off. Harris comes forward to block it.
Full, on the pads. Clipped past mid on for one.
Length, on the pads again. Worked down to fine leg for one.
Broad is targeting the pads now. Harris works it past mid-wicket for a couple. Should have been three and Harris wanted it but Marnus sent him back.
On a length, on middle. Blocked out.
A solid defence by Harris to end the over.
Back of a length, 148 kph, at the body. Marnus dabs it down towards short mid-wicket.
A length ball, around the hips. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it just past leg slip and the ball races towards fine leg. They get a single.
Wood hits the deck hard and bowls this one on off stump. Harris manages to block it out.

FIVE WIDES! That's the third time the ball has flown over Jos Buttler's ​​​​​​head. Short delivery, 143 kph, banged in around middle. The ball just takes off after pitching and races away into the fence as Buttler can't get a glove to it.
On middle, defended out.
A length ball, on off. Harris nudges it towards covers and sets off for a quick single. Ben Stokes slips a bit while picking up the ball but he's okay.
On a good length, around off. Marnus defends it back onto the deck.

Close! Pitched up, on middle. Marcus Harris tucks it towards mid-wicket and wants the quick single. James Anderson is quick to attack it and has a shy at the striker's end. Marnus Labuschagne puts in the dive and survives.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne goes on the back foot and pushes it wide of mid on for a couple.
Broad goes a bit wider this time and Marnus makes an easy leave.
Slightly pitched up, well outside off and the ball shapes away late. Marnus shoulders arms.
This time the ball swings the other way. Length, outside off and the ball nips in after going past the batter.
Length again, outside off. Left alone.
Anderson comes on and goes full straightaway. Marcus Harris punches it off the middle of the bat but can't get it past short mid off.
Down the leg side, Harris looks to flick but misses.
Right on the money from James Anderson. On off and Harris defends it off the front foot.
A length ball, on top of off. Harris stays solid in defense.
Anderson goes fuller and bowls it around the off pole. Marcus Harris presses forward and drives it towards cover.
Attacking the pads this time, Harris tucks it away nicely through mid-wicket and picks up a couple.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Beaten! Nice and full, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne is drawn into the drive but gets beaten.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Closer to the off pole and Marnus Labuschagne tucks it to the leg side.
Good length, on off. Tapped to point.
Fuller this time, on the fifth stump. Marnus Labuschagne comes forward to block it.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Blocked out by Harris nicely.
Short of a length, outside off. Harris pushes it to point.
FOUR! Another nice drive from the bat of Harris! He leans into it and drives it to the cover fence.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Good-length delivery, on off. Harris stays in the crease to block it.
Length and drifting down the leg side. Marnus misses the glance.
Back of a length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to block but gets the inside edge on the pads.
Fuller, around off. Tapped to mid on. No ball called. This is quite frustrating to be honest.
Nicely flicked away off his pads by Marnus Labuschagne. But Leach chases it from square leg and dives to stop the boundary. Three runs and that brings up the 100 for Australia.

Confusion in the middle! Length, on off. Tapped to square leg. They both take off for a single but Harris decides against it and tries to get back. But, he slips and falls on the deck. He recovers and gets back in. The throw comes at the other end but the fielder misses.
Short of a length, around off. Pushed to point.
Full, on off. Blocked out.
Length, outside off. Left alone.
Wide outside off and Marnus Labuschagne leaves it. He brings out his typical bat swipe this time.
Inside edge on that. Full and on the pads. Marnus Labuschagne looks to flick but gets the inside edge on the pads.
Good length, wide outside off. Left alone.
Wide enough to be left alone again.
Fuller and outside off. Driven past covers for a couple.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Short of a length, on middle. Tapped to the leg side.
Goes short this time but Harris ducks under it.
Length, around off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Cut away hard! Short of a length, outside off. Harris slashes it past point for a boundary.
Beaten! Length ball, around off. Harris is beaten as he looks to block.
Fuller, around off. Blocked out.
Full again, on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it under his eyes.
Marnus is chirpy out there, says 'oh, a bit of bounce.' A length ball, on middle and this one bounces a bit extra. Marnus manages to tap it back onto the deck.
Length again, outside off this time and left alone.
Fullish ball, on off and this is pushed back towards the bowler.
On a length, around middle. Marnus tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Leach starts from 'round the wicket and bowls a floater around the leg stump. Marcus Harris goes on the back foot and keeps it out on the leg side.
On a length, on off. Harris defends it out.
A tad bit short, on middle. Harris stays deep in his crease and punches it past mid on for a single.
Flatter delivery, on off. Marnus plays it off the back foot towards covers and sneaks in a quick single.
This is pushed through on a length, around middle and leg. Harris blocks it out.
The crowd is really getting into it now.  Around the leg stump, Harris goes deep in his crease and keeps it out on the leg side.
Nicely bowled! A length ball, in that channel around off. Marnus Labuschagne makes an assured leave.
A touch fuller, outside off. Anderson wants Marnus to drive but the latter makes another good leave.
Length again, well outside off and Marnus isn't going to play at that one.
Anderson is getting good bounce and carry from the surface and is clocking over 135 kph now. Anderson goes fuller this time but once again it's outside off. Marnus shoulders arms.
On top of off and defended back towards the bowler.

Short of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne plays a controlled pull shot in front of square and pierces the gap between mid-wicket and mid on. He comes back for the second with ease. James Anderson shows his frustration by kicking the bowling crease.
On middle, nudged away on the leg side.
Flatter delivery, around off. Harris keeps it out off the back foot.
On a length, around off. Harris goes on the back foot and pushes it out on the off side.
Around leg stump, Harris works it through mid-wicket for an easy single.
On off, eased towards the cover region.
Quicker one, darted into middle stump. Marnus manages to keep it out. It's Nelson for 1.

OUT! CAUGHT! Keeping James Anderson on for a longer spell has worked. Good-length ball, on off and this is angled across the left-hander. Marcus Harris is caught on the crease as he goes neither on the back foot or on the front foot. The ball goes off the outside edge as Harris looks to push at it and goes straight towards first slip. Joe Root makes no mistake and the Nelson superstition proves unlucky for the Aussies. Harris has to depart after setting himself up for a big innings, he will be disappointed with that.
Howout: c Joe Root b James Anderson

Commentary: Fullish ball, around off. Steven Smith leans into the drive and gets it through covers for a couple.
Length ball, outside off and this one zips through after pitching. Smith leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on off. Smith taps it towards mid on.
Slightly pitched up this time from Anderson but it's well outside off. Smith makes the leave and the ball nips back in after going past the batter.

Length again, around off and this one nips back in sharply. Steven Smith looks to defend it off the front foot but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Luckily for him, there's no short leg. End of a testing over from James Anderson.
FOUR! Back of a length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne punches it off the back foot and times it perfectly through extra cover. He picks up a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Inspired move from Joe Root to get Mark Wood into the attack. Wood hits the length hard and angles it into off stump. The ball just straightens a bit after pitching and that is enough to get the edge. Marnus Labuschagne is on the back foot and looks to block it out but gets undone by the ball holding its line. The ball goes off the outside edge and Jos Buttler makes no mistake behind the stumps. The floodgates are certainly open now for England but can they take advantage? Usman Khawaja is in at number 5.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Mark Wood

Commentary: Wood bangs it in, down the leg side. Khawaja ducks under it.
Good-length ball, around middle and leg. Khawaja defends it out.
Length again, just down the leg side. Usman Khawaja isn't interested in having a poke at it.
Wood comes from 'round the wicket for the final delivery and hurls across a length ball, at the body. Usman Khawaja defends it out towards mid on.
Fuller, around off. Smith gets forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Worked to the leg side by Smith.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Beaten! Fuller, just outside off. It lands and then shapes away. Smith is stuck in the crease while looking to block and is beaten.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Fuller and outside off. Left alone. Maiden by Anderson.
Back of a length, coming back in with the angle. Khawaja leaves it on length and the ball goes over the stumps.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Nicely driven but to the man at short cover.
A bumper, outside off. Left alone.
Full and down the leg side. Khawaja misses the flick.
Fuller, on off. Pushed to covers/
Stokes bowls it full, around off. Smith pushes it to mid off.
Length, around off. Smith blocks it out.
Full, on off. Smith blocks it from the crease.
Stokes keeps it full but Smith is solid in his defence.
On a length, on the stumps. Blocked out.
Very full again, on off. Smith digs it out.
Short of a length, on the body. Blocked out.
Short, on the body. Worked to short leg. Khawaja stays on naught.

FOUR! He gets off the mark! The English bowlers did build up the pressure as they did not give a single run in 25 deliveries. Khawaja was probably expecting the short one and pulls it nicely to the square leg fence.
On a length, around off. Blocked out.
Length ball, angling across off. Khawaja leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Fullish ball, outside off. Steven Smith looks to drive it through covers but gets it off the inner half of the bat towards the bowler.
A length ball, wide of off stump. Smith leaves it alone.
On top of off, Smith goes back and across to defend.

FOUR! Shouts of 'catch' but Steven Smith gets it well wide of the man at deep backward square leg. If the plan was to trap him, they could have placed a man in front of square. Short, on the body. Smith pulls it away for a boundary.
On off, Smith strides out to defend.
A length ball, around off. Smith walks across his stumps and defends it towards mid on.
A length ball, angled into the off stump. Khawaja manages to keep it on the leg side.
NO BALL! Broad goes fuller and bowls this one on the fifth stump. Usman Khawaja shoulders arms. A no ball is called as Broad oversteps.
On a good length, around off and just angling away after pitching. Khawaja keeps it down towards point.
Right in that channel, outside the off pole. Khawaja makes an assured leave.
Length again, on top of off. Usman Khawaja edges it down towards the point region.
This is angled at the pads. Khawaja keeps it out towards mid on.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Wood fires a full one, on off. Smith gets forward and blocks it.
Full and fires on the pads. Smith blocks it to the leg side.
Well bowled. Short of a length, around off. Smith looks to swipe it away but gets hit on the body. The ball loops up and goes over the stumps.
First runs of the day. Back of a length, on off. Smith pushes it past cover for one.
A touch fuller, angling across off. Khawaja lets the keeper collect this one.
On a length, on middle. Khawaja clips it towards leg gully.
Nice and full, on off. Smith pushes it towards mid off.
Length, outside off. Left alone.
Shorter, around off. Smith gets the inside edge on the pads while looking to block.
Just outside off yet again but Smith leaves it with ease.
Length, outside off. Smith gets forward to block it.
On off and Smith punches it right back to the bowler.
On a length, just outside off. Khawaja leaves it alone.
A touch fuller, but quite straight. Khawaja blocks it to the leg side.
Well bowled. At 145 kph, on a length, around middle. It goes away with the angle and hits Khawaja on the pads as he looks to block.
This is good bowling. Wood is consistently bowling that line and taking it away from the left-hander. Khawaja though is leaving it alone for now.
No room again whatsoever. Blocked out back to the bowler by Khawaja.
Khawaja gets the inside edge as he looks to block this length ball on off.
Fuller, around off. Smith blocks it from the crease.
Bit of bounce on that. Length and outside off. Smith gets the outside edge past the diving third slip for a couple.
Nice and full, around off. Smith goes for the drive but gets the inside edge towards mid-wicket.

Two more and Broad is a bit frustrated. Not at any of the fielders, but at the situation. He wants to bowl to Khawaja here but isn't able to. Length, around off. Smith gets the outside edge past gully for a couple.
Another couple as this is flicked towards deep backward square leg.
Short of a length, on the pads. Smith taps it towards square leg.
Runs are coming now. Full and outside off. Khawaja drives it past point. Leach chases it and keeps it to three.
Wood bowls one down the leg side. Left alone by Smith.
Ooh! There are two fielders in the deep and as expected, Wood bangs this in. Smith though manages to keep his pull shot along the ground and gets it to deep square leg for one.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Length, around leg. Khawaja works it past mid on for one.
A bit fuller, on off. Smith blocks it from the crease.
Lands outside off and comes back in with the angle. Khawaja leaves it though.
Back of a length, just outside off. Blocked out.
Full, on middle. Khawaja works it past mid on for one. A single and Broad will have to bowl to Smith again.
Length, on off. Blocked out.
Full and way down the leg side. Smith leaves it in his typical fashion. Gets down on his knee and has hit bat high up.
Down the leg side again but Smith goes for the glance this time. He misses it though.
Anderson starts with a length ball, on off. Khawaja blocks it from the crease.
Fuller and straighter. Khawaja taps it to the leg side.
Bit of bounce there! Length, lands on middle and angles away. It shoots up after landing. Khawaja looks to block but gets hit high on the bat. That took a piece off the surface.
Fuller, around off. Blocked out.
Full and on the pads. Khawaja gets some pad on it. It goes towards the keeper for one.
Beaten! Fuller and in the corridor of uncertainty. It shapes away just enough to beat Smith's attempted defence. Well bowled.
Full and on the pads. Clipped to mid on.
Darted on the pads again. Khawaja works it to deep square leg for one.
Tossed up, on off. Blocked out.
Nicely driven past covers for a couple.
Flatter, on off. Blocked out.
A single as this is pushed to long off.
This is pitched up, around off. Smith presses forward to block but gets an inside edge down to fine leg and picks up a single.
On a good length, on off. Left alone.
On the pads, Khawaja keeps it out to short mid-wicket.
Slightly pitched up, just outside off. Khawaja makes a watchful leave.
And again. An action replay of the previous delivery as Khawaja makes yet another assured leave.
Around middle and leg, Khawaja blocks it out.
Tossed up, around off. Smith pushes it down to long off for an easy single.
Flighted delivery, on middle and leg. Usman Khawaja flicks it past mid-wicket for a single.
Slowed up, on middle. Smith defends it out towards mid on.
Around the off pole, this one grips and turns away a bit. Smith shoulders arms.
Flatter delivery, around middle. Smith defends it out.
On the pads and flicked straight to square leg. Smith looks for the quicks single but is sent back.
On middle, this is pushed with soft hands towards mid on for a quick single.
Anderson goes fuller this time, on off. Smith defends it off the front foot.
A good-length ball, on off. Smith goes on the back foot to block it out.
FOUR! A glorious way to start off after the break. Pitched up from Anderson and Smith plays a beautiful straight drive back past the bowler and into the fence.
On a good length, outside off and left alone.
On top of off, kept out on the leg side by Smith.
Shortish ball, on leg stump. Khawaja goes on the back foot and works it towards midwicket for one.
On off, Smith leans forward to defend.
This is pushed through, on off. Smith defends it towards mid on.
Fuller, around middle and leg. Smith wrists it through mid-wicket and picks up a single.

FOUR! Really cheeky from Usman Khawaja. Leach comes over the wicket and tosses it up, around the middle stump. Khawaja gets into position quickly and plays the reverse sweep. The ball races away to the point fence.
On middle. Kept out.
Back of a length, on off. Smith keeps it down towards short leg.
Full, on off. Smith defends it right under his eyeline.
Fullish ball, on off and shaping in a bit. Smith hangs back and defends it towards sill mid on.
On the pads, this is tucked away behind square on the leg side for two.
In that channel outside off and this one just holds its line. Smith leaves it alone.
This is angled in at the off stump. Smith stays solid in defense.
Floated up, well outside off. Khawaja drives it towards cover-point.
Flatter one, darted into middle and leg. Khawaja keeps it out.
This is angled into the off pole and Khawaja manages to block it out.
On the pads, nudged onto the leg side.
Flatter again, on middle and leg. Khawaja dabs it down to short leg.
Flighted ball, outside off and Khawaja slices his cover drive towards point. End of a maiden over from Jack Leach.
A length ball, around that fifth stump line. Left alone.
Angled into middle and leg. Steven Smith shuffles across a bit and gets inside the line of the ball. He then flicks it fine and collects a couple of runs.
Good-length ball, on middle. Smith works it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Nicely bowled. In that channel around the off pole and trying to bring it back into the left-hander. The ball holds its line and Khawaja makes a good leave.
A length ball, outside off. Usman Khawaja shoulders arms.
Anderson comes 'round the wicket and hurls across a length ball, on off. Usman Khawaja stays solid in defense.
On a length, around off. Smith pushes it gently on the off side and sneaks in an easy single.
On middle, Khawaja is pushed back to defend.
Quicker one, on off. Khawaja defends it off the back foot.
Fired in, around off. Khawaja manages to keep it out on the off side.

FOUR! Uppish but safe! Short and wide, Usman Khawaja cuts it off the back foot and gets it past backward point. The ball runs away into the fence. With this, the fifty partnership also comes up between these two.
Loopy ball, around off. Khawaja presses forward to defend.
On middle and leg, tucked away towards square leg for one.
A length ball, on top of off. Khawaja defends it solidly off the back foot.
An attempted short ball, angled down leg. Khawaja pulls it towards fine leg and picks up a single. Anderson falls over on his follow-through but fortunately hasn't hurt himself.

Oops... mixup, safe! You don't want to take the big Ben on, do you? A length ball, around off. Smith drives it on the up and gets it through covers. Ben Stokes and another fielder from point go after it with Stokes getting there first. Normally, in such big grounds, you take one on the throw and Smith turns blindly for the third. But Stokes is super quick to first, stop the ball and then turn around quickly to release it as well. Khawaja sees that and sends Smith back, who had almost come a quarter of the way down the track. Excellent decision from Uzzie. The throw was right at the stumps to Buttler.
A good-length ball, on off. Smith hops back and taps it towards short cover for a quick single.
Anderson goes fuller and bowls this one around the off pole. Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
A flighted delivery, outside off. Smith strides out to defend.
This is pushed through a bit quicker, on off. Smith blocks it back to the bowler.
Darted into middle stump, Smith blocks it out
Leach gives this one a bit more air and bowls it around off. Smith nudges it out on the off side.
Tossed up, around middle and leg. Steven Smith uses his wrists to flick it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Flatter one, on middle. Usman Khawaja goes on the back foot to work it on the leg side for a run.
Short, on middle. Khawaja sits under it.
Another bumper from Stokes and Khawaja lets Buttler collect the ball.
He takes him on now! That should give Stokes some hope. Short, on the body. Khawaja is not able to keep his pull shot down. It goes in the air but drops short of fine leg for a single.
'Round the wicket and short again. This does not rise up though and Smith swipes it along the ground to deep mid-wicket for one.
On a length, on the pads. Khawaja gets hit on the pads while looking to flick. The ball rolls away and a leg bye is taken.
A solid block by Smith from the crease.
Tossed up, on middle. Khawaja blocks it from the crease.
Shorter, on the pads. Tucked to short fine leg.
Better. Angling across off. Khawaja gets a bit of extra bounce but manages to keep it out.
Down the leg side again and nicely worked past square leg for one.
Fuller, on middle. Smith blocks it towards mid on.
Tossed up, on off. Smith gets forward to block it.
Short of a length, outside off. Khawaja misses the cut.
Another short one, angling down leg this time. Khawaja moves across and lets it through to the keeper.
And again. Stokes digs in another short one, down the leg side. Khawaja leaves it alone.
Ouch! That must have stung! This time Stokes directs the bumper at the body of Khawaja. The ball hurries onto the batter and Khawaja can't get away from it in time. He gets a blow on the shoulder.
Short again, down the leg side and Khawaja is able to leave it alone.
Shortish ball, around the hips. Khawaja pulls it down to fine leg for a run.
Darted on the pas. Worked to the leg side.
Fuller, on off. Khawaja blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up, on the pads. Khawaja works it past square leg for a single.
Fuller, on off. Blocked out.
On the pads and flicked away towards square leg for a single.
Quicker and flatter, around off. Usman Khawaja looks to defend but ends up getting an inside edge on it.
Short of a length, on the body. Pulled down to fine leg for one.
This rises a bit more on Khawaja but he pulls it along the ground to fine leg for one.
Short, down the leg side. Smith sits under it.
Ouch! Short and on the body. Smith wants to duck under it but the ball doesn't rise up as much as he expected. He gets hit on the gloves.
Pulled away to deep mid-wicket for one.
Khawaja ducks under this one with ease.
Fuller, on middle. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, around off. Blocked out.
Pushed past covers for one by Smith.

DROPPED! That should have been taken! The on-air commentators were wondering how Leach was going to take a wicket here! Caught in the slips was not the most likely scenario but that almost happened! Flatter, angling across off. Khawaja is a bit lazy in his defence and gets the outside edge. The ball brushes the left thigh of Buttler and goes to first slip. That deflection probably put Root off. He tries to catch the ball to his right but drops it. It rolls away and a single is taken.
On the pads. Clipped to mid on for one.
Darted on the pads. Worked away to the leg side for one.
Shorter, on off. Khawaja leaves it.
Short and on the body but left alone again.
Pulled down towards fine leg for a single.
Bumper again, on middle. Smith taps it towards short leg. The ball bounces on its way to Haseeb Hameed.
Down the leg side with the short one and Smith is not bothered.
Smith gets a full one, outside off. He pushes it past covers for one.
A single down to long off.
Fuller, on off. Khawaja pushes it to long on for one.
Tossed up, on off. Smith blocks it away.
Shorter, around off. Smith pushes it past covers for one.
Darted around off. Pushed away by Khawaja.

Misfield. Full, on middle. Nicely worked towards short mid on. That should be a dot ball but Haseeb Hameed fumbles and the ball rolls away. You can just sense the frustration and anger in Jack Leach's mind. Hameed apologizes to Leach on the misfield but Leach is not even interested in looking at him. He just takes his cap from Haseeb and looks at the big screen instead, to see the replay of that ball.
Length ball, on the pads. Khawaja gets rapped on the pads and the ball rolls away towards fine leg. Leg bye.
Fast. 147.5 kph, full and on the pads. Pushed to mid on for one.
Length, on the pads. Tapped to the leg side.
A bumper, across off but Khawaja sways away from the line of the ball.
Fuller, angling across off. Khawaja covers the stumps and leaves it alone.
Full again, on middle. Worked past square leg for one.
Fuller, on middle. Smith gets forward to block it.
Darted on middle. Pushed towards mid on.
Tossed up, around off. Smith pushes it to long off for one.
Flatter, around off. Khawaja blocks it from the crease.
Khawaja gets down the track and blocks it towards cover.
Fuller and outside off. Khawaja drives it nicely to the left of deep cover. Zak Crawley gets across and keeps it to a couple. That brings up the 200 for the hosts and they are in a good position now.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Nice and full, on off. Smith gets forward to block it.
Fuller, on off. Smith works it towards mid on. The fielder moves to his right and keeps it to one.
Shorter, on off. Tapped past short leg by Khawaja.
Tossed up, on off. Khawaja drives it past the dive of Malan. It goes to long on for one.
Flicked through mid-wicket for a single by Smith.
Loopy ball, on off. Smith gets forward to block.
Smith gets this past mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up, on middle. Khawaja works it to mid-wicket. There is a bit of confusion regarding the single but they do not go for it.
Full, on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Shorter and outside off. Khawaja cuts it past point for a couple.
Darted on the pads. Worked past mid-wicket for one.
Fuller, on middle. Smith pushes it back to the bowler.
Shorter, around off. Punched to cover.
Nice and full, on off. Pushed to mid off.

Fifty for Smith. He came in when his team was in a bit of trouble but he has been really good so far. His 33rd fifty in Tests and he would want to put on a big knock here. He gets there by punching this flatter ball to deep cover for one and gets a nice applause from his home crowd.
Sucker delivery as they call it. A high full toss, outside off. Cut away to deep cover for one.
Full, on the pads. Flicked away for one and that is Lunch on Day 2!
FOUR! A real loosener to start with from Jack Leach. Short and wide, Steven Smith rocks back and cuts it into the point fence.
A tad bit short and wide again. This time Smith eases it through covers for one.
On the pads, flicked onto the leg side for a single.
On off, Smith defends it off the front foot.
This is slightly quicker and drifted into middle. Smith defends it out with soft hands.
Slower through the air but short again. Smith caresses it through the cover region for a run.
Quicker one, down the leg side. Smith dabs it down towards leg gully.
A touch short, around off. Smith backs away and plays it through cover-point for one. The hundred partnership is up between these two.
Flatter one, on off and punched off the back foot towards cover.
FOUR! Too easy. This is dragged down, on middle. Usman Khawaja has ample time to rock back and pull it away into the mid-wicket fence.
Flighted delivery, around off. Khawaja pushes it out on the off side.
Quicker one, around off and cut away towards cover-point.
Close! A length ball, around middle and this one goes on with the angle. Steven Smith moves across his stumps and misses the flick. The ball goes past the leg stump.
This is outside off and Smith isn't going to have a poke at that one.
Anderson goes a bit fuller and bowls an in-dipper, around off. Smith hangs back and eases it towards mid on.
A length ball, around the fifth-stump line. This is angled in but shapes away a bit after pitching. Smith makes a watchful leave.
Lovely shape! Around off and this one shapes away beautifully from the right-hander. Smith lets it through to the keeper.
This is spilled well down the leg side. Anderson starts off with a maiden with the second new ball.
A length ball, wide of off stump. Khawaja shoulders arms.
Fullish ball, angled into middle stump. Khawaja stays solid in defense.
Pitched up, on off. Khawaja punches it towards short mid on. The fielder over there dives to his right and makes a half-stop. They do get the single.
Length again, around off. Smith drives it straight to mid off.
Fullish ball, on off and this is driven firmly towards mid on.
Very full, around off. Smith jams it out towards short cover.
Around middle and leg, pushed gently towards mid on for a quick single. Good running.
A length ball, outside off. Smith gets right behind the line of the ball to block it.
Length again, drifting onto the hips. Smith flicks it to fine leg for one.
On off, Khawaja taps it back towards the bowler.
Nicely bowled! A length ball, around middle and going across the left-hander. The ball holds its line after pitching but Khawaja makes a good leave.
Fullish ball, around off. This is nudged out on the off side.
FOUR! A half-volley, outside off. Steven Smith leans into the cover drive and gets it through cover-point for a boundary.

NOT OUT! What was Steven Smith doing there? A fullish ball, angling down leg. Smith thinks that it is definitely going down the leg side and offers no shot. The ball crashes into the back leg and Stuart Broad seems confident. The umpire shakes his head but the review is taken. As no shot was offered impact doesn't matter but the ball was just sliding down the leg stump. England lose the review but it was certainly worth a go.
Fullish ball, around off and left alone.
Ooh! Broad pitches it up a bit, around the off pole. The ball is angled in but after pitching, moves away and bounces a bit extra as well. Steven Smith is lucky not to have edged that one.

FOUR! There is a leg slip in place but Smith does not care. A short ball, angled into the body, Smith swivels and pulls it to the left of leg slip and beats fine leg to his right. Now, that is called precision in bisection.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Stuart Broad has the last laugh and England have the breakthrough they were so desperately looking for. Stuart Broad bowls a length ball, outside off and this is angled in. Just like a couple of deliveries earlier, the ball straightens after pitching. Steven Smith shuffles a bit and is caught on the crease. He is completely undone by the away movement and this time ends up edging it. Jos Buttler dives down to his right and takes a fine catch. The partnership is broken and can England now capitalize?
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Stuart Broad

Commentary: A length ball, wide of off stump and left alone.
Back of a length, on off. Khawaja hops back to defend.
A short ball from around the wicket and angled at the body. Khawaja manages to defend it out.

A short ball, down the leg side, Usman Khawaja swivels and helps it towards fine leg for a couple. Should have been just a single but Mark Wood does not sight the ball at first and that allows the batters to come for the second.
Fuller, around off, driven towards mid off.
Around off, solidly defended.
Broad hits the deck on a length, lands outside off and comes back in. Green gets in half a stride and blocks it.
Fuller, around off. Green pushes it to point.
Ooh! Length ball, lands around off and comes back in. Green thinks that this will move away too and leaves it. But the ball comes back in and hits him high on the pads.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Blocked out.
Off the mark! Broad pitches it up, around off. Green gets the outside edge past point for one.

Now, Khawaja gets a fifty. Came in as the replacement for Head and he is looked very secure out there. He did get a reprieve off the bowling of Leach though. Fuller, around off. He looks to block but gets the inside edge past square leg for a couple.
Fuller, around off. Blocked out.
Wood hits the deck on a length, on off. Green blocks it well though.
Fuller, lands outside off and shapes away a touch. Left alone by Green.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.

FOUR! Did that carry? Tough chance but neither of the slip fielders make an attempt to go for it! Length ball, right on the off pole. Green is stuck in the crease while looking to block but gets the outside edge. The ball drops just short of first slip and goes past him for a boundary. Root could have gone for it by diving forward. But it should have ideally been Stokes to go for it from second slip but his back probably didn't allow him too.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Fuller, around off. Pushed towards mid on for one.
Length ball, around off. Green blocks it from the crease.
Jagging back in from outside off, on a length. Green gets hit on the body while looking to block.

OUT! TAKEN! Gone this time and Stuart Broad has brought England right back in the game! He serves a length ball, around off. Green does not reach the pitch of the ball and goes out with his hands looking to block that one. There is a hint of shape and he gets the outside edge. This time the ball carries and Zak Crawley takes a good low catch at third slip. This is more headache to the Aussie selectors. Cameron Green is an allrounder but cannot score with the bat these days. That raises the question - should someone like Mitchell Marsh, who is in the form of his life, be ignored? But then, Green is bowling tremendously and holding onto his place. Possibly another question then - why not make Carey bat above him?
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Stuart Broad

Commentary: On a length, around off. Carey leaves it on length and the ball goes over the stumps.
Fuller and outside off. Carey plants his front foot forward and then leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around off. Khawaja blocks it from the crease.
Play and a miss! Short of a length, outside off. Khawaja goes for the pull but the ball sneaks under his bat and goes through to the keeper.

FOUR! Not where one should bowl right now. Wood fires it down the leg side. All that Khawaja has to do is help it on its way to the fine leg fence and he does so with ease. One of the mistakes England might be sucked into doing is concentrating ONLY on the new batter (s). They should not forget that even though Khawaja has not looked at his absolute best, this is a ground which he knows very well. He has consumed enough balls and if England let him off the hook, he might just make them pay later.
On a length, around off. Blocked out with ease.
Wood goes over the wicket and bowls a full one, on off. Blocked out by Khawaja.
Full, on off. Khawaja defends it with ease.
Length and outside off. Carey puts in a nice stride only to leave it alone.
On a length, closer to the off pole. Carey stays in the crease and pushes it past gully for one.
Too full, on off. Khawaja blocks it.
Well-controlled shot. Short of a length, outside off. The ball stays a bit low and Khawaja pulls it all along the carpet to deep square leg for one.
Good-length ball, on the fifth stump. Carey gets forward and looks to block it with soft hands. So despite getting it off the shoulder of the bat, the ball rolls towards the slip cordon.
Carey puts in another nice stride to block this length ball.
Fuller, angled across off. Blocked out.
Wood bends his back and bowls a short one, on middle. Khawaja sits under it.
Beaten! Short of a length, angling across off. Khawaja is glued to his crease while looking to block. The ball goes on with the angle and zips past the outside edge.
Length, on middle. Blocked out.
Short ball, around off. Khawaja ducks under it.
Extra pace on that! Length delivery, on middle and leg. Khawaja looks to block but there is extra bit of bounce and pace on that. He manages to awkwardly keep it out towards square leg for one.
On a length, around off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Thumping pull shot! Khawaja takes the short ball on and pulls it along the ground past mid-wicket for a boundary. A great shot.
Well bowled. Broad slips this full, on middle. Khawaja is caught on the crease and gets the inside edge on the pads.
Fuller, just outside off. Khawaja prods forward but leaves it.
Beaten this time. Length and angled across off. Khawaja looks to block but the ball zips past the outside edge. Broad cannot believe that it did not take the edge.
Full this time, on the pads. Blocked out with ease by Khawaja.

FOUR! Inside edge this time! Back of a length, on middle. Carey is neither going forward nor going back to block it. He looks to tap it out from the crease but gets the inside edge. The ball runs to the fine leg fence.
A similar delivery but this time Carey taps it with soft hands towards point.
Well bowled! It lands on a length, outside off and just takes off. Carey looks to block it at first but pulls his bat out at the last moment.

Whoa. What happened there? This lands on a length, just outside off. Carey stays in the crease to block but the ball simply does not rise up. It keeps very low and goes towards the keeper. Buttler is taken by surprise too and gets hit on the left hand due to the awkward bounce.
Length, on the pads. Worked past square leg for a couple.
A touch fuller, on middle. This time Carey gets hit on the pads while looking to block.
Short of a length, around off. Blocked out.
Short of a length, on the body. Khawaja works it past square leg for one.
Length ball, on the pads. Blocked out by Carey.

Appeal for LBW! Fuller ball, on middle. Carey gets hit on the pads while looking to block. There is an appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Root asks Anderson if there was some bat on it. The bowler is unsure but they do not go for the review. Good decision as the replay shows that there was an inside edge.
Short of a length, on middle. Blocked out.
Short of a length, around middle and leg. Carey works it to square leg.
Short and wide, cut away off the back foot through the cover region for a couple.
Fuller delivery, on off. Khawaja drives it straight towards extra cover.
On a length, on middle. Khawaja is pushed on the back foot to defend.

Nicely bowled! Slowed up, around the off pole. Usman Khawaja has a poke at it but doesn't know if it will turn in or go on with the natural angle. In the end, the ball goes straight and agonizingly past his outside edge.
Flighted ball, on off. Khawaja strides out to defend.
Tossed up, around off and pushed out on the off side.
A length ball, around off. Carey drives it on the up but straight towards extra cover.
On a good length, around middle. Carey leans forward to defend but the ball just bounces a bit extra and goes on to hit Carey high on the pads.
Short of a length, well outside off. Left alone.
Anderson digs one in around chest height, over the leg stump. Carey pulls it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Length again, on top of off. Khawaja edges it down with soft hands and gets it through backward point. They get a single.
James Anderson is time and again extracting a bit of extra bounce. Good-length ball, on middle. Carey looks to go forward but adjusts well to the awkward bounce and gloves it down on the off side.
Slowed up, on the pads. Khawaja turns it towards square leg.
On middle and leg, this is clipped away towards mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery, around off. Usman Khawaja puts out a stride to defend.
Tossed up, around off and inviting the batter to drive. Khawaja does play the cover drive but the fielder at short cover makes a great stop down to his left.
Flatter one, on middle. Blocked out.
On off, Khawaja defends it off the front foot.
Good-length ball, over middle. Carey looks to turn it on the leg side but closes the face of the bat a tad bit early. The ball goes off the leading edge and back onto the deck.
Slightly fuller, outside off and left alone.
Back of a length, on off. Carey goes on the back foot to tap it towards cover-point.
Length again, around the top of off. Carey lunges forward to push it towards cover.
A length ball, on the pads. Carey nudges it onto the leg side.
On a good length, on middle. Carey looks to defend off the front foot but gets it off the inner half of the bat towards short mid-wicket.
On the pads and worked through mid-wicket by Khawaja for one.
Slightly fuller, on middle. Alex Carey slogs it to deep square leg for another single.
Dragged down, outside leg stump. Usman Khawaja misses out on that one as he misses the pull shot.
Quicker one, around off and blocked out by Khawaja.
Slowed up, on middle. Khawaja pushes it out on the off side.
On middle, eased through mid on for a single.
Anderson comes 'round the wicket and digs in a short one at the body. Usman Khawaja swivels and pulls it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Good cricket all around. Fuller ball, on middle. Alex Carey leans in and plays a lovely straight drive. James Anderson does really well to get down and field it off his own bowling.
Here's that awkward bounce once again. On a good length, around middle. This one nips back in a bit and bounces a bit extra as well. Carey gets hit around the ribs.
A touch shorter, around leg stump. Carey looks to get it away on the leg stump but gets hit on the gloves due to the extra bounce.
A length ball, around off and angling across. Easy leave for Carey.
On off, pushed towards extra cover.
On a length, darting into off. Khawaja keeps it out on the off side.
Slightly tossed up, around off. Khawaja works it towards wide mid off for a single.
Darted into middle and leg. Carey gets an inside edge onto the pads but there's no short leg.
FOUR! A juicy half-volley, around middle and leg. Alex Carey makes a bit of room and lofts it right back over Root's head for a boundary.
Flatter dleivery, on middle. Carey pushes it back to the bowler.
Carey tries to get funky now. Fuller one, around off. Alex Carey plays the reverse sweep but cannot beat the backward point fielder to his right.
FOUR! Tossed up, outside off. Usman Khawaja cover drives this one into the vacant sweeper cover fence.
On middle, blocked back to the bowler.
There are huge vacant spaces on the off side and Khawaja is exploiting them. Quicker one, full and around off. Khawaja leans into the drive and gets it past extra cover for a couple.

FOUR! This is really poor from Jack Leach as he is bowling it just too full at the moment. Around middle, Khawaja strides forward and creams this one through extra cover for the second boundary in the over.
Flatter delivery, on middle. Khawaja defends it off the back foot.
Fullish ball, around off. Khawaja nudges it towards cover-point for a quick single.
Angled at the pads, Khawaja works it through mid-wicket for one.
Around off and played towards point.

OUT! TAKEN! Joe Root with the golden arm. This is a huge wicket for England as it exposes the tail of the Australian batting lineup. Nicely tossed up, around off. Alex Carey looks to slog it over the mid-wicket fence, against the turn and ends up giving his wicket away. The ball goes off the top edge and is skied towards the mid on region. The fielder, Jonny Bairstow runs behind from mid-wicket and slides in to take a fine catch. Can England now run through the Australian lower order?
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Joe Root

Commentary: On middle, kept out by Khawaja.
Darted into middle and leg, Khawaja keeps it out.
FOUR! Usman Khawaja is in fine form here. A touch short and wide, Khawaja latches onto it and cuts it away into the point fence.
Fullish ball, on off. Cummins mistimes his drive towards mid on.
A well-directed bouncer at 144 kph, over middle stump. Pat Cummins manages to get his head out of the way.
Another short ball, with a bit of heat on it. Cummins isn't fazed by it though.
Good-length ball, around off. Cummins leaves it alone and the ball just flies after going past the stumps.
Well bowled! Wood angles in a length ball at 144 kph, around off. The ball straightens after pitching. Cummins looks to have a poke at it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length again, a bit wide of off stump this time and left alone.
Darted on the pads. Khawaja works it to deep square leg for one.
Tossed up, on middle. Cummins gets forward to block it.
Darted on middle. Cummins goes back and blocks it.
Tossed up, down the leg side. Worked to square leg.
Darted down the leg side. Cummins kicks it away.
Flatter, on off. Cummins goes back and blocks it.
Short of a length, around off. Khawaja rises with the bounce and taps it past mid-wicket for one.
Bumper, down the leg side. Cummins leaves it alone.
Beaten! Length ball, just outside off. Cummins looks to block it from the crease but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Short of a length, on middle. Cummins sways away from the line of the ball.

Beaten again! Fuller, outside off. Cummins looks to block with his feet glued to the crease but it goes past the outside edge. The look on Wood's face says it all. He has gone past the edge so many times but hasn't had much luck. Tough game for a fast bowler.
Short ball, down the leg side. Cummins misses the flick.
Tossed up, on off. Blocked out.
Fuller, on off. Khawaja blocks it with ease.
Shorter, on off. Defended off the back foot.
Nicely driven to deep cover for a single.
Flatter and way down the leg side. Left alone.
Shorter, on middle. Worked to square leg.
FOUR! He moves into the 90s! Short of a length, around off. Khawaja rocks back and pulls it nicely to the square leg fence.
Short and way outside off. Cut away to deep cover for a single.
Full, on the pas. Blocked out.
On a length, outside off. Cummins leaves it alone.
Short ball, on off. Cummins sways away from the line of the ball.
Full, on the pads. Cummins blocks it from the crease.
Tossed up, around off. Khawaja gets forward and blocks it.
Nicely driven to deep cover for one.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Cummins gets off the mark after 23 balls by working this to long on and that brings about applause from the crowd.
Tossed up, outside off. Khawaja drives it to deep cover for one. 300 up for the hosts now.
Full, on the pads. Worked to long on for one.
FOUR! He moves to 99 now! Short and outside off. Khawaja rocks back and cuts it to the point fence for a boundary. Just 1 away from what will be a well-deserved ton.
Full ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Tossed up, on off. Cummins gets forward and blocks it.
Full, on off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Smashed down the ground! Short and outside off. Cummins rocks back and hammers it down the ground for a boundary.
FOUR! Again! Too full this time. Cummins clears his front leg and thumps it over mid on for a boundary.

BOOOOOOOOOOOOOO goes the crowd! Oh Patrick, why did you have to take the single on the last ball? But like a perfect teammate, Usman Khawaja smiles. Full, outside off, deliberately looped up, the skipper lunges and drives it beautifully. Extra cover makes no effort whatsoever in trying to stop the ball, conveniently giving the single. Oh... mind games, tell ya. England want Uzzie to stay on 99 at Tea.
Loopy ball, on off. Cummins blocks it out.
Full and on off. Cummins blocks it out.
Here we go! Shorter, on off. Cummins pushes it past covers for one. Usman Khawaja is on strike now. The crowd is getting in on it.

THERE IT IS! Usman Khawaja, the comeback king! His 9th Test ton and boy, he is pumped about it! Coming back in the side after 3 years and he has proved his worth! Off comes the helmet and he soaks in the massive applause from the crowd. His family is in the stands and it must be a special feeling for him. Stokes applauds him too, good sporting spirit by the big man. This has been a brilliant knock by him. Usman Khawaja was put under a bit of pressure late on Day 1 when the English bowlers had their tails up but he weathered that. Runs came freely after that and he deserves every bit of this applause. He gets to his ton by working this short ball towards deep square leg. Anderson's chase and dive cuts the ball off. But they get three runs.
Shorter and outside off. Cummins goes for the cut but gets the outside edge to third man for three.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out. That is Tea on Day 2!

FOUR! Well, that's aggressive from the skipper. A loosener to start with from Stuart Broad as he bowls a half-volley, outside off. Pat Cummins leans in and creams it through covers for a boundary. Cracking start after the break.

NOT OUT! Great comeback delivery from Stuart Broad. A length ball, around middle and nipping back in sharply. Pat Cummins goes back and across as he looks to block it out but misses. Cummins gets rapped on the pads and Broad is celebrating without even turning back. The umpire raises his finger and Cummins reviews it straightaway. Ball Tracker confirms that the ball was sliding down the leg side and it ends up being a great review by the skipper. Broad cannot believe it but the decision has been overturned.
Broad goes fuller this time and bowls it around off. Cummins drives it to wide mid off but can't get it through.

FOUR! Lucky! Broad tries to nip the ball in from outside off and does just that. Pat Cummins is caught in two minds on whether to play at it or not. He leaves his bat dangling till the last moment and finally looks to leave. The ball though goes off the edge and through the slip cordon. The ball races away into the third man fence and Broad is left frustrated.
On a good length, around off. Left alone.
Length again, around middle. Cummins dabs it down on the leg side.
Flatter, around off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, on middle. Khawaja taps it to the leg side.
Similar line and length. Khawaja blocks it from the crease.
Flatter, on off. Khawaja gets the outside edge past point for one.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Cummins blocks it.
A single as this is pushed to long off.
Back of a length, around the off pole. Pat Cummins hangs back and keeps it down towards backward point.

Nicely bowled! Stuart Broad is really steaming in and putting in an effort at the moment. Angles in a short ball, at the body. Pat Cummins looks to get his head out of the way but ends up getting hit on the arm. That must have stung.
Another short one, outside off. This time Cummins is able to leave it alone. Buttler does well to leap up and pouch it.
Slightly fuller this time, around off. Cummins looks to drive it through covers but gets it off the inner half of the bat towards mid on.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Stuart Broad has been bending his back in this over and does get his man in the end. Broad bangs in another short ball and it's just perfect. The ball is short enough to trouble the batter and is right at the body. Pat Cummins is taken aback by the steep bounce and tries to get out of the way but there's not much time for that. Jos Buttler leaps high once again and takes it well over his head. The visitors think the ball came off the glove but the umpire shakes his head. It is reviewed and UltraEdge shows that the ball just flicked the glove and the decision is reversed. Pat Cummins has to depart but he has done a decent job.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Stuart Broad

Commentary: A length ball, outside off. Mitchell Starc makes a leave.
Drifted into middle. Khawaja strides out and defends it back to the bowler.
Leach goes fuller and bowls it on off stump. Usman Khawaja presses forward and pushes it through the gap at extra cover. He picks up a couple.
Leach pulls back his length a bit and bowls it on off. Khawaja is pushed on the back foot to block it out.
This is sliding down the leg side and it is a bit short as well. Khawaja jabs it past backward square leg and gets back for another two.
Around middle and leg, flicked away on the leg side for one.
Leach gives it a bit more air and drifts it into off stump. Mitchell Starc strides out and pushes it away on the off side.
Short of a length, on leg stump. Usman Khawaja goes on the back foot and tucks it away towards backward square leg for one.
LEG BYE! A length ball, on the pads. Starc looks to flick it away but misses. The ball comes off the thigh pad and rolls onto the leg side. The batters get an easy leg bye.
Right on the money from Broad! Length again, on top of off. Khawaja stands tall and punches it towards mid off.
Around middle, Khawaja blocks it out.
Broad is attacking the stumps right now and keeps it around top of middle stump. Khawaja stays solid in defense.
Yet another length ball, around middle and leg this time. Khawaja defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up, on middle. Mitchell Starc drives it down to long on for a single. Jack Leach is really struggling to find any rhythm out there.
Fuller, around off. Pushed to cover.
Khawaja comes down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.
Angled into the pads, Khawaja works it through square leg for another easy single.
On a length, sliding into leg stump. Starc works it past mid-wicket for a single.

Another sort of half-volley, outside off from Jack Leach. Usman Khawaja leans into the cover drive and gets it through the infield. The ball is racing away into the fence but the fielder from deep point gets across to left quickly and keeps it down to two.

Just short! Stuart Broad is looking like the only one who might pick up a wicket here. Back of a length, around leg. Starc looks to turn it on the leg side but closes the face of the bat a bit early. The ball goes off the leading edge and falls short of Haseeb Hameed at short cover.
Good-length ball, over off stump. Mitchell Starc makes a well-judged leave.
FOUR! Top-quality shot! Broad goes fuller this time and looks to clean Starc up. Starc though leans into the straight drive and times it perfectly past the bowler for a boundary.

DRAMA! Broad has appealed for a caught behind but umpire Rod Tucker has shaken his head. With 1 second left on the clock, Root has reviewed. Well, nothing on the UltraEdge. The ball has missed the bat. But could this be LBW? It has hit Starc above the knee roll. UMPIRE'S CALL ON HITTING THE WICKETS! Wow. Nearly a 5-fer for Broady. A length ball, around off, Mitchell Starc looked to play the same shot as he did on the previous ball, straight back down the ground. But he missed and the ball went off something to Buttler. Now, there was a faint noise and Buttler made a small sign of appealing but was not too sure. Broad was sure, as always and Root too, from first slip, seemed convinced that there was a sound. They took the review and at that time, Broad snubbed Starc, 'Didn't you hit that? I heard a noise for sure.' Now, the first replay clearly showed the bat away from the ball but Shane Warne on air reckoned that could be LBW. And dear me, Warney was not entirely wrong! England retain their review as another positive in all this drama.
Broad digs in a short ball, at the body. Starc mistimes the pull shot towards mid-wicket but does get the single.
On a good length, 138 kph and around middle. Usman Khawaja hops on the back foot to defend it out.

Edged away! Leach tosses one up, outside off. Mitchell Starc presses forward and looks to drive it through covers but gets a thick outside edge which flies past first slip. Joe Root gives the chase and cuts it off before the ball ends up in the third man fence. The batters comes back for the third with ease.
Flatter delivery, around middle and blocked out.
Another round of applause from the crowd as Usman Khawaja crosses 3000 Test runs. On off, this is pushed nicely through covers for a couple.

Usman Khawaja is bringing out the variety now. Leach goes fuller, on off. Khawaja plays the reverse sweep and gets it behind point. The ball is racing into the fence but once again it is cut off. They get three.
On off, Starc defends it off the front foot on the off side.
Leach comes from 'round the wicket and bowls it on the pads. Starc nudges it out.

Khawaja is seeing it like a football out there. A length ball, on leg stump. Usman Khawaja stands tall and punches it on the up, right back past the bowler. The fielder from mid on gives chase and cuts it off. The batters get yet another three.

In the air...safe! Now Mitchell Starc looks to take on Broad. Shortish ball, around off. Starc throws the kitchen sink at it as he looks to go downtown. The ball goes off the top edge and flies over the vacant cover region. They take a couple.
Around the top of off stump, Starc pushes it out on the off side.
A length ball, outside off and left alone by Starc.
Broad angles in a length ball from 'round the wicket and tries to attack the pads. Starc works it through mid-wicket for a single.
Short of a good length, outside off. Khawaja stands tall and eases it through cover-point for one.
Fuller, around off. Pushed down to mid off.
Fuller, on off. Khawaja drives it to deep cover for one.
Tossed up, on off. Starc blocks it out.
Full, on off. Blocked out nicely.
Darted on the pads. Starc clips it towards fine leg for three runs as the fielder chases it down.
Flatter, on middle. Blocked out.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out past cover for one.
On a length, around off. Blocked out by Khawaja.
Short of a length, on off. Blocked out.
On a length, on middle. Worked past mid-wicket for one.
Back of a length, around off. Blocked out by Starc.
Length, outside off. Starc taps it towards the slip cordon.
Angled into middle and leg, Khawaja flicks it through square leg for a single.
Tossed up, around off. Starc strides forward and keeps it out on the off side.
Nicely flighted, outside off. Mitchell Starc caresses it through covers for a single.
FOUR! You can't bowl there to a batsman who has been out there for son long. Dragged down, on the pads. Usman Khawaja shuffles a bit and pulls it through square keg and into the fence.
A loopy delivery now, on the stumps. Khawaja waits for it and pushes it down the ground for one.
On off, Khwaja presses forward to defend.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
On the pads and Khawaja flicks it away for a single.
Length, on the pads. Starc works it to mid-wicket.
Short of a length, on the body. Starc clips it to fine leg for a single.
Fuller, around off. Khawaja drives it nicely through covers for a couple.
Almost chopped on! Short ball, on off. Khawaja gets the inside edge as he looks to pull. The ball goes past the stumps and Buttler makes a good diving stop.
Short of a length, outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, on off. Starc blocks it from the crease.
A bit closer to the off pole and fuller. Blocked out with ease.
This is a sharp bouncer. On off but Starc sways away and Buttler leaps up and catches it.
Fuller ball, around off. Blocked out.
Wood fires a full one, on the pads. Starc clips it to the leg side.
On a length, outside off. Left alone by Khawaja.
Fuller, on off. Khawaja drives it nicely to mid off.
Short of a length, outside off. Khawaja lets Buttler collect this.
A touch wider again and Khawaja won't chase it. They are not in a hurry at this point.
A touch fuller and closer to the stumps but wide enough for Khawaja to leave it.
Yet another comfortable leave by Khawaja to end the over.
Length ball, angling across off. Left alone.

FOUR! Unlucky for Wood! A sharp short one, on the body. Starc is taken aback by the bounce and looks to leave it. But the ball hits the gloves and goes over the keeper. Boundary. That also brings up the 50-run stand between these two.

NOT OUT! Tell you what, my heart goes out to Wood. He bowls with everything that he has and creates chances but doesn't get the luck going his way. Short, on the body. Starc goes for the pull but misses. There is a sound as the ball goes past him and up goes the finger! But Starc reviews it straightaway. UltraEdge shows that the ball brushed the arm guard and not the gloves!
Short of a length, on middle. Turned to mid-wicket.
Bouncer down the leg side. Starc goes for the pull again but misses.
Fuller, on off. Pushed to mid off.
Nice and full, outside off. Khawaja leans into it and pushes it to cover.
Back of a length, outside off and Khawaja leaves it alone.
Again it;s a bit shorter in length, around off. Usman Khawaja goes on the back foot and punches it towards cover.
Anderson goes fuller this time, around off. Khawaja sets up for the extravagant cover drive but ends up just about pushing it towards the cover region.
Shorter in length, a bit of width on offer. Khawaja doesn't play at it.
Full and wide, Khawaja shoulders arms. End of a maiden over from James Anderson.
Full, around off. Starc leans into the drive and gets it past mid off for a couple.
A pacy short ball, over leg stump. Mitchell Starc ducks under it.

FOUR! What happened here? Attempted short ball from Wood, at the body. Starc hangs back and this one doesn't rise up much. Starc pulls it towards square leg where Jonny Bairstow just doesn't pick the ball and the ball goes past him into the fence.

It's just not Mark Wood's day! Another short ball at 147 kph, at the body. Starc looks to keep it down on the leg side but its just that bit of an extra bounce that surprises him. The ball hits Starc flush on the glove and pops up towards the vacant silly point region.
Shorter in length, around off and angling across. Mitchell Starc doesn't play at it.
Back of a length, around 145 kph and around off. Starc goes on the back foot and dabs it down towards backward point.
Fuller ball, on the pads. Khawaja works it past square leg for one.
Length ball, on the pads. Tapped past mid on for one.
Length ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Short of a length, on off. Blocked out by Khawaja again.
Fuller and angling across off. Khawaja leaves it with ease.
Nice and full, around off. Khawaja gets the outside edge towards gully.
Wood cranks it at 147 kph, full and angling across off. Starc looks to punch it through covers but the ball goes past the outside edge. Wood has a wry smile on his face.
A sharp short one, on middle. Worked towards mid-wicket.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Full, on the pads. Starc works it towards deep backward square leg for one. Jonny Bairstow cuts it off and gets a nice cheer from the crowd while walking back to his mark.
Fuller, on off. Blocked out.
Short of a length, on off. Blocked out yet again by Khawaja.
In the air, but safe! A bit of extra bounce as Broad bangs it in back of a length. Starc gets the leading edge but the ball loops up and drops short of gully.
Length ball, angling across and left alone.
Length, on the pads. Starc works it towards fine leg for one.
FOUR! Top shot! A bit short, on off. Khawaja rocks back and pulls it to the mid-wicket fence.
