OUT! BOWLED! A 5-wicket haul for Broad! He has bowled really well and deserves this. Would be fair to say that he is probably the only one who has looked like he would take wickets here. But what a knock by Usman Khawaja. A sensational ton that has put his team well on top now. Not easy to score runs rightaway after coming back in the side after a big gap but he has delivered for his team. He bowls it full, on off. Khawaja looks to punch it away but his feet are a bit lazy on this one. It takes the inside edge and the ball crashes into the stumps. He walks off to a well-deserved standing ovation from his home crowd.
Howout: b Stuart Broad

Commentary: A length ball, around the off pole and this one shapes away a bit. Nathan Lyon has a poke at it but doesn't get his bat anywhere close to the ball. End of a successful over from Stuart Broad.
Back of a length, at the body. Starc keeps it down towards mid-wicket.
A pacy bumper at 144 kph. Mitchell Starc manages to duck under it as the ball flies over his head.
Short of a good length, around leg stump. Starc punches it off the back foot towards mid on.
Short again, at the body. Starc goes on the back foot and works it past short fine leg for a single.
Another short ball, around middle. Nathan Lyon hops and keeps it out on the leg side.

FOUR! Classy shot from Nathan Lyon and the 400 is up for Australia. Wood goes short again, around off but thsi one sits up nicely for the batter. Lyon hangs back and fetches it from outside off before pulling it in front of square. The ball races through mid-wicket and Lyon picks up a boundary.
A short ball, down the leg side. Starc doesn't even have to duck under it to let it sail over his head.
Fuller, around off. Starc pushes it past covers for one.
FOUR! Nice Gary! A full ball, on off. Lyon clears his front leg and hits it over the bowler's head. The ball trickles as it reaches the fence.
Oh ho! A mighty heave and a miss! Length ball, around middle. Lyon looks to send the ball sailing in the crowd behind the mid-wicket fence but misses.
Length ball, on off. Lyon clubs it away past mid-wicket for a couple.

SIX! BOOM! That is out of here! Wow, what a shot by the spinner! Length ball, on off. Lyon rocks back, lines himself up and heaves it over the mid-wicket fence. Cummins has a big smile on his face as Australia declare on 416 for 8!

Pat Cummins steams in and gets the ball moving right away. On a good length, in that corridor of uncertainty. The ball shapes away after pitching. Haseeb Hameed is caught in two minds but eventually leaves it alone.
England are off the mark. Cummins goes full, trying to attack the pads. Hameed clips it nicely through mid-wicket. His partner Zak Crawley wants two but Hameed isn't interested. Just a single then.
Cummins pitches it a bit further up but it's well outside off. Crawley makes an easy leave.
Length this time, on top of off. Zak Crawley plays it late and defends it under his eyeline.

Ooh! That one came back in a fair bit. On a length, around 139 kph and just outside off. Zak Crawley puts out a stride and looks to leave but the ball nips back in sharply off the surface and raps Crawley on the pads. It's a bit too high and hence no appeal.

FOUR BYES! My word! That one took off like an airplane! This one is delivered on a good length, just around the off pole. Zak Crawley makes a leave but the ball just shoots up after pitching and flies over the keeper's head for a boundary. No chance that Carey was getting to that one.
Starc pitches it up, around off and looks to bring the ball back into the right-hander. Hameed stays solid in defense.
A length ball, on off. Hameed plays it with soft hands towards covers and sets off for a quick single. Good running.
Angled across the right-hander and pitches just around off. Crawley reads it off the hand and makes an assured leave.
Starc goes fuller, around middle. Crawley defends it off the front foot.

FOUR LEG BYES! Mitchell Starc looks to attack the pads but gets it a bit too straight. Zak Crawley looks to flick but misses. The ball goes off the pads and flies past the diving keeper and into the fine leg fence.
Shorter in length, around off and this one angles across the batter. Crawley leaves it alone.

Edged but safe! Good-length ball, on off. Haseeb Hameed goes backward and looks to push at it but does so with hard hands. The ball goes off the outside edge and luckily for Hameed, falls short of Cameron Green at gully.
Length again, 141 kph and slanting down the leg side. Hameed looks to defend it off the back foot but gets beaten.
Back of a length, outside off stump. Hameed lets it through to the keeper.
Cummins looks to bring the ball back in but bowls this one wide of off stump. Hameed makes yet another leave.

Ooh! That one swung late and swung a long way back in. Cummins keeps probing outside the off stump and finally goes for the big in-dipper. Hameed leaves it as it is a fair bit outside off but the ball swings in late and goes past the off stump.
Another inswinger, this time around middle. Hameed looks to flick but the ball just flies after pitching and goes down the leg side. Good take from Carey to his left.
Back of a length, outside off and left alone.
A length ball, down the leg side. Crawley misses the flick.
Good-length ball, around the fifth stump. Zak Crawley shoulders arms. Starc looks like he is lacking a bit of rhythm.

NO BALL! Oh no! The celebrations in the Aussie camp are halted. Just as Starc was looking a bit under par with his bowling, he bowls an absolute ripper. The ball is delivered on a good length, just around the off pole and the batter has to play at it. The ball angles across a bit and bounces a bit extra as well. Zak Crawley gets the faintest of outside edges and the ball flies towards first slip. David Warner takes a sharp catch around his chest and Crawley seems to be out on a duck yet again. But hold on, the umpires check for the front foot and Starc doesn't have anything behind the line. It looks very close though as the foot is very close to the line when it makes an impact but the TV umpire feels that it is a no ball. Crawley walks back to the middle and the Aussies cannot believe it.
Full and on the pads. Zak Crawley clips it to deep square leg for a couple.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Nice and full, on off. Equally nice defence by Zak Crawley.
Cummins is charging in here. A length ball, outside off and the ball zips through. Haseeb Hameed makes the leave. 5 more to go!
Pat Cummins angles this one into middle stump but Hameed defends it out. His heart must be pounding real hard right now.
Good-length ball, around off and shaping in a bit. Haseeb Hameed hops on the back foot and plays it late.

Well, that one swung a mile once again. Cummins goes wide of the crease and bowls an inswinger which pitches around the off pole. The ball just nips in sharply off the surface but Hameed gets right behind the line to block it out.

Close but not close enough. Cummins goes fuller this time and catches Hameed on the crease. Hameed looks to go back and play it late with soft hands but gets an outside edge which goes towards the gully region.

Hameed survives and that will be it for Day 2! Pat Cummins ends a probing spell with a length ball, angled into middle and leg. Hameed hangs back and just about manages to keep it out. With a bit of luck and perseverance, England do not lose any wickets.
Starc steams in with the SCG crowd cheering him up. He serves a full ball, around off. Zak Crawley pushes it towards mid on.
Nice and full, around off. Crawley puts in a nice stride to block it.
A lot wide as Starc wants Crawley to drive this but the batter leaves it.
First runs of the day. Short and down the leg side. Zak Crawley toe-ends the pull shot. It goes past the keeper and down to fine leg for one.
Ooh! Length ball, lands on off and angles away. The ball goes just past the off pole as Hameed leaves it.
Starc bowls a short one, around off. Left alone again.
Top shot! Full, on off. Driven nicely past mid off by Zak Crawley. Marnus Labuschagne gives it the chase and dives to stop the ball. But given the long boundaries at the SCG, the batters run four!
On a length, outside off. Left alone this time.
Fuller ball, on the fourth stump. Crawley gets on top of the ball and blocks it.
Too high. Lands on a length, outside off and comes back in. Zak Crawley gets hit on the thigh while looking to block.
Well bowled! This shapes away! On a length, just outside off. Zak Crawley is forced to play and he looks to block it from the crease. The ball shapes away just enough to beat the outside edge.
Back of a length, around off. Blocked out with ease.

DROPPED! Alex Carey! Could he have left it for Warner to catch it? That was going straight towards Warner at first slip! Length ball, angling across off. Haseeb Hameed looks to block it from the crease. The ball takes the outside edge and flies away. Carey dives full length to his right and gets his glove to it but the ball doesn't stick. It would have gone straight to Warner had Carey not gone for that.
Length ball, on off. Hameed leaves it on length.
FOUR! Nicely played. This will frustrate Starc! Back of a length, just outside off. Hameed nicely guides it past point and gets a boundary.
Back of a length, on middle. Blocked out.
Fuller, landing on middle and tailing back in. Worked towards mid on.
On a length, on middle and leg. Blocked out.
Length, outside off. Zak covers the stumps and leaves it.
Back of a length, just outside off. Crawley looks to block it from the crease but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Sliding down the leg side this time and Crawley misses the flick.
This comes back in after landing outside off. Zak Crawley nicely covers the stumps and leaves it.
Short ball to Crawley, around off. He thinks about pulling it at first but drops his hands in the end.
Left alone this time as this is quite wide outside off.
Full and down the leg side. Hameed misses the flick.

OUT! BOWLED! Luck favors Starc this time! He bowls a full one, on off. This one shapes back in a bit. Hameed once again goes for the straight drive without much feet movement. That leaves a big gap between the bat and the pads. That is more than enough for the ball to sneak through and castle the middle stump! Hameed's poor run in the Ashes continues.
Howout: b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Fiery stuff! Back of a length, around off. Malan goes back to block it but the ball rises a bit more than expected. Malan manages to keep it down though.
Full and down the leg side. Malan misses the flick.
Full, outside off. Malan leaves it.
Full again, down the leg side. Malan misses the glance again.
Shorter, on off. Crawley sways away from the line.
Length ball, on off. Zak Crawley taps it out.

Put down! That was a very tough chance though! Length ball, on off. Crawley got the inside edge on the thigh guard. The ball went flying to the right of Harris at short leg. He went to his right, got his hand to it but it popped out.
Length ball, around off. Left alone.
FOUR! Lovely stroke. Full, outside off. Zak Crawley plants his front foot forward and drives it through covers for a boundary.
More runs! Zak drives this full ball past mid on now. Boland chases it and puts in the slide. He stops it just before the ropes. Three runs.
Length ball, around off. Left alone.
Sharp inswinger now! Length is a bit short and Crawley gets hit on the body as he looks to leave this one.
Ouch! That rises sharply! Lands on a length, on leg and just takes off. Zak Crawley sets himself up for a nice defence but gets pinged on the gloves. That will sting for sure.
Fuller, on middle. Pushed to mid on.
Length ball, on the pads. Crawley taps it to the leg side.
FOUR! Wow. Where did that come from? A short one and one would have expected him to duck under it. But Crawley pulls it aerially over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Full, on the pads. Malan taps it away.
Length, on off. Malan blocks it towards cover.
Fuller and straighter. Worked past square leg for a couple. Malan is off the mark.
Cummins bangs it in, around off. But Malan sways away nicely.
Length, angling across off. Malan leaves it with ease.
Clipped down to fine leg for an easy single.
Lovely cover drive by Malan but straight to short cover.
Length delivery, on off. Malan blocks it.
Another nice defence from the crease off Malan's bat.
Short of a length, outside off. Malan goes back and across looking to cut it but misses.
Short, down the leg side. Left alone.
Back of a length, sliding down the leg stumps again. Malan misses the flick.
Length, lands outside off and comes back in. Left alone.
Another one jagging back in but a good leave by Crawley.
Nice and full, on off. Crawley gets forward to block it.
Short of a length, lands outside off and stays a bit low. Zak ends up inside-edging the pull shot on his thigh pad.
On a length, around off. Blocked again.
Short of a length, just outside off. Crawley goes back and blocks it.
Green starts with a length ball, outside off. It is left alone.
Length again, outside off, this one bounces more than expected and Malan misses his cut.
Touch fuller, angling outside off. Malan shoulders arms.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Short of a length, outside off. Malan stands tall and lets it through to the keeper.
Maiden over! Another short ball, followed by another leave by Malan. Good carry to Carey.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Nicely driven but straight to mid off. This was full and on off.
BEATEN! Right on the money! A length ball, outside off. Zak Crawley looks to defend on the front foot but gets beaten on the outside edge.
This one jags back in, on a length, on middle. Crawley looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Outside off and Crawley leaves it alone.

OUT! TIMBER! Both the openers are gone! What a delivery from Scott Boland! This one lands on off and nips back in sharply. Zak Crawley is committed to his drive but gets beaten on the inside edge and the ball disturbs the stumps. Another sloppy start for the openers of England. Boland's dream start to Test cricket continues.
Howout: b Scott Boland

Commentary: A length ball, outside off. Malan leaves it alone.
Another leave by Malan. It was way outside off.
In the air but way short of mid-wicket, Malan didn't time it at all. Short ball, on middle. Malan mistimes his pull towards mid-wicket.
Fuller ball, outside off. Malan defends it with an angled bat on the off side.
Carey catches this over his head! Length ball, outside off, this one bounces off the crack. Malan leaves it alone.
A short ball, on off. Malan sways away from the line. Probing lines from Green.
A full ball, on off. Root defends it to point. Australia will love another wicket here.
This one comes with the angle, full and on middle. Root pushes it to mid off.
Length and on off. Defended out.
A length ball, on off. Root guides it to gully and Green does well to dive to his left and stop it.
Fuller ball, on off. Root shuffles and blocks it late.
A length ball, outside off. Root works it on the off side. Six maiden overs in a row.
Length ball, way outside off. Easy leave.
On a length, outside off. Malan chops it to gully.
Short of a length, slanting outside off. Malan shoulders arms to it.
A huge appeal for LBW but height might have saved him! A length ball, this one jags back in sharply and hits Malan on the pads as he looks to flick. Australia opt not to take the review.
A length ball, on off. Malan defends it out.
Make it seven maiden overs in a row! Length ball, outside off. Malan leaves it alone.

OUT! EDGE AND GONE! Australia get the big wicket of Root at the brink of the Lunch break! A duck for Root on today's menu as well. This is on a length and way outside off. The pressure building up over the last few overs gets to Root. He goes for the cut shot but manages an outside edge to second slip where Steven Smith catches it very high. He ain't dropping those. Scott Boland living his life at the moment.
Howout: c Steven Smith b Scott Boland

Commentary: Length ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Stokes stays back and defends it out.
Length ball, outside off. Stokes covers his stumps and leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Lovely bowling! A length ball, coming with the angle. Ben Stokes looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
JAFFA! Another great over from Boland! Length ball, outside off, a late outswinger. Stokes is squared up as he tries to defend. Eight maiden overs on the trot. Pressure on England piling up.
Length ball, on middle, some steep bounce and Malan gets hit on the gloves as he looks to defend.
Full and outside off. Left alone.
Full ball, outside off. Malan offers no shot to it.
Again gets hit on the gloves! England can't make a way for themselves! Short of a length, on middle. Malan gets hit on the gloves.

OUT! TAKEN! This is a trap from Australia! What a session for the hosts! They have both the big wickets before the morning session and Australia will enjoy the Lunch more. A length ball, angling on middle and leg. Malan shuffles and tries to flick it away. It goes more of the inside edge towards leg slip where Usman Khawaja makes a full-length dive forward and takes a sharp catch. That will be Lunch on Day 3.
Howout: c Usman Khawaja b Cameron Green

Commentary: Full and down the leg side. Left alone and that makes it 9 maidens on the trot.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Back of a length, just outside off. Stokes gets across and blocks it.
Stokes takes a step down the track and works it towards mid-wicket.
Boland bowls it full, on off. Blocked out by Stokes.
Almost a run! Stokes works this length ball towards mid on. Both the batters take a step down the track but turn back again.
Beaten! On a length, lands outside off. Stokes gets across looking to block it but the ball zips past the outside edge. 10 maidens now.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Beaten! That is a peach! On a length, just outside off. Bairstow is beaten as he looks to block.
Fuller, on off. Blocked out nicely.
Full and down the leg side. Jonny Bairstow misses the flick.
Good-length delivery, right on the off pole. A solid block by Jonny.
Was there some bat on that? Doesn't seem like it. Short of a length, on off. Jonny Bairstow goes for the pull but gets hit on the body. The ball lands short of the dive of Green from gully.
Length ball, on the sixth stump. Nicely left alone by Stokes.
Nice and full, on off. Blocked out.
Length ball, around off. Another easy leave for Stokes.
Length but down the leg side. Stokes misses the glance. He is moving around quite a bit in the crease hoping that Boland will change his length and line.
First runs in 71 balls and the SCG crowd cheers! Length ball, around off. Stokes gets the outside edge past cover for one.
Fuller, around off. Jonny Bairstow gets the outside edge towards gully. Michael Hussey jokes about this being an expensive over for Australia.
Fuller and angling across off. Stokes is forced to play but the ball goes past the outside edge.
This is wider and Stokes makes a leave.
Nicely punched but straight towards short mid off.
On a length, fifth-stump line. Stokes shoulders arms.
FOUR! Thumping shot! Overpitched, on off. Stokes shows the full face of the bat and drives it nicely to the long off fence. A no ball too as Cummins oversteps.
Length, around off. It stays a touch low but Stokes blocks it.
FOUR! Put away! Short and on middle. Stokes rocks back and pulls it all along the ground to the square leg fence.
More runs for England! Worked past point for a couple by Jonny.
Length, on off. Jonny Bairstow gets forward to block it.
Full, on off. Pushed to mid on.
Fuller, on off. Pushed to mid off.
Back of a length, outside off. Chopped away but Lyon makes a good stop at point. Wonder when he will get to bowl.
On a length, on off. Tapped to covers by Bairstow.
Back of a length, outside off. Left alone.
Short of a length, outside off, left alone.
Length, on middle. Stokes taps it to mid-wicket.

DROPPED! Full, on off. Stokes hits it back to the bowler. It comes at nice height to Cummins but he is in his follow through so has less time to react. He gets his hands down but it pops out. He tries to take it again as he is falling down but doesn't hold onto it.
Fuller, on off. Blocked out.
Length, just outside off. Stokes leaves it with ease.
On middle, tucked away to mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Stokes shuffles way across and pushes it to mid on.
135 clicks! On a length, on middle. Blocked out.
FOUR! Too straight! Full and on middle. Stokes drives it nicely and wide of mid on for a boundary. England getting along smoothly.
On a length, on off. Stokes steps across and defends it under his eyes.
A length ball, this one jags back in and hits Stokes as he steps down and looks to defend but gets hit high on the pads.
A length ball, on middle. Defended out.
Length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow looks to defend it very late and it takes the shoulder of the bat, through the slip cordon and a single is taken.
On middle, blocked out on the leg side.
Length and on middle. Stokes defend it solidly.
Full and outside off. Stokes drives it aerially and towards deep cover for three runs.
Length ball, shaping in and Bairstow slaps it to covers.

NOT OUT! WHAT HAPPENED THERE? Did that hit the stumps? But the bails are intact well. A length ball, this one comes back in sharply with the angle. Stokes shoulders arms to it. The ball goes onto hit the stumps but the bails do not clip off. It did hit hard but still, the bails are in place. Wow! Stokes takes the review but as there was no bat or even a brush of pads there, the on-field decision is overturned. No idea why the umpire raised the finger. The ball was miles away from the pads too.
Full, on middle, pushed to mid on.
Full and around off, pushed to covers for a couple.
Length and outside off, Left alone.
This is full and on off. Stokes is early as he tries to defend and hits it to mid off.
FOUR! Up and over! A length ball, outside off. Stokes smashes it off the toe end of his back but enough to clear mid off. Boundary.
FOUR! Good shot! A full ball, on the pads. Jonny Bairstow flicks it through square leg for a boundary. Runs coming nicely for the visitors now.
Short and down the leg side. Left alone.
Very full and on middle, pushed to mid on.
Length ball, angling across. Bairstow leaves it alone.
Short of a length, on the hips, extra pace too. Bairstow tickles it to fine leg for a couple.
On a length, on middle. Blocked out.
Green serves a short ball, on middle. Stokes sits under it.
Touch fuller, on middle. Stokes blocks it back on the deck.
What a delivery! Angles a full ball, on the pads. Ben Stokes looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads.
WIDE! Bangs a bouncer on middle. Left alone. Wided.
Full and outside off. Left alone by Stokes.
A length ball, on middle, some extra pace here from Green. Stokes gets hit on the gloves due to the extra bounce. Drops his bat in pain.
On a length, on off, Blocked out.
Short of a length, around off. Bairstow shoulders arms.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone. Carey collects it very low. The pitch is playing it uneven here but the repair work is going on decently for England. Still a long way to go.
Full ball, outside off. Bairstow gets an inside edge as he looks to drive it. The ball goes to the fine leg region and a couple of runs are taken.
Short and way down the leg side. Bairstow lets it through.
Length ball, around the fourth-stump channel. Jonny Bairstow shoulders arms to it.
On the pads, this is tucked away to mid-wicket.
Sharp bounce! Short of a length, just outside off. Stokes looks to block it at first but the ball shoots up and goes past the outside edge.
Back of a length, around off. Stokes works it past point for three runs.
Full, on off. Nicely blocked out.
Length ball, on off. Bairstow taps it down on the deck.
Nice and full but wide enough to be left alone with ease.
Full, on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
FOUR! Easy pickings. Full and on the pads. Stokes flicks it nicely to the square leg fence.
FOUR! Again! Full, on off. Stokes punches it nicely to the long on fence.

FOUR! Oh boy! We could be in for an exciting phase of play if Stokes keeps batting like this! Short and on off. He rocks back and pulls it to the mid-wicket fence. That brings up the 50-run stand and these two have looked quite good in the middle.
Length, outside off. Left alone.
Fuller, around off. Stokes comes forward to block it.
Punched off the back foot past cover for one.
Stokes dances down the track and blocks it out. This could be very exciting.
Tossed up, on off. Stokes gets the inside edge past short leg.
Loopy ball, on off. Stokes comes down the track and drags it past mid-wicket for a couple.
Flatter, on off. Blocked out.
Full and on the pads. Worked to deep square leg for a couple.
Darted on off. Stokes goes back and blocks it.
Nicely driven to short cover by Jonny.
On a length, on middle. Bairstow looks to block but gets the inside edge on the pads.
Fuller, outside off. Driven uppishly but wide of cover for a couple.
Short, around off. Left alone.
Back of a length, angling across off. Bairstow leaves it alone.
Full, on the pads. Worked to fine leg for a single.
Loopy ball, on off. Worked to short leg.
Tossed up, around off. Jonny Bairstow goes for the sweep but gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but not given. Impact would have been an issue.
Flatter, on off. Tapped to short leg.
Full, on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, around off. Jonny drives it past covers for a couple.
FOUR! Nicely done! Tossed up, on off. This time Jonny Bairstow connects the sweep and finds the square leg fence.
Length and on middle, nudged on the leg side.
Inside edge! A length ball, it lands outside off and nips back in. Stokes gets low to defend but it takes the inside edge to the leg side for a single.
On middle, this is flicked to deep square leg for one more.
FOUR! Beautifully driven! A full ball, outside off. Stokes leans and drives it through covers for a boundary.
On a length, on middle, pushed to mid on.
Now Stokes comes down and across to block it out.
FOUR! Good shot! This is short and way outside off, width on offer and Bairstow lashes on it and the ball races away to the point fence.
Full and on middle, Blocked out.
FOUR! Boundaries flowing! Pre-meditates and paddles this full ball to the fine leg fence.
Slower, full and on middle. Blocked out.
Again width given. Bairstow drives it to point.
Tossed up, on off, tucked to mid-wicket.
A length ball, outside off. Stokes shuffles and blocks it out.

Length ball, on off. Stokes comes down the track and whips it through mid-wicket. The fielder gives a chase and does well to flick it away. Three runs. It also brings up FIFTY for Ben Stokes. Well played. A great knock under pressure by England's southpaw.
Fuller on off, pushed to mid on.
BEATEN! Lovely delivery! A length ball, in the channel of uncertainty! Jonny Bairstow looks for a juicy drive but misses.
Full and on off, pushed back to Boland who does well to get low and stop it.
Length and on off. Blocked out.
Full and on middle, this is flicked to mid-wicket for a single.
Flatter and on middle. Bairstow gets low and defends it towards short leg.
Slightly short, on off. Jonny Bairstow rocks back and blocks it.
On middle, nudged to square leg.
FOUR! Races away! Tossed up, on middle. Jonny Bairstow gets on his knee and sweeps it to square leg for a boundary.
Short and outside off. Bairstow cuts it through point and collects three runs. He is eyeing his half-century as well.
This one skids through, on off. Bairstow gets behind the line to block it out.
Length ball, outside off. Blocked out.
Almost a yorker, on middle. Bairstow jams it out to square leg for a brace.
FOUR! Bairstow is dealing in boundaries! A length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow guides it through backward point for a boundary.
Fuller and on middle, pushed to mid on.
Angles it on the pads, this is flicked to deep mid-wicket for a couple. 8 runs coming off the over.
Flatter, on off. Blocked out.
Fuller, on off. Blocked by Stokes again.
Loopy ball, around off. Stokes pushes it to cover.
A single as this is pushed to long on.
Loopy ball, down the leg side. Bairtsow offers his pads to this.
Shorter, outside off. Cut away to point.
Fuller ball, outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, way outside off. Stokes takes a step down the track and leaves it.
Too full and too wide. Left alone.
Length again, but Stokes leaves this wide one easily.
On a length, on off. Stokes blocks it out.

Dot to finish the session and that ends the session! England have not a single wicket and have scored 99 runs! Length ball, down the leg side. Boland slips after bowling that and Stokes leaves it. That will be Tea on Day 3!
Tossed up, on off. Blocked out.
Fuller, around off. Pushed to cover.

Great effort by Smith! Tossed up, on off. Bairstow gets low and Smith, who is at first slip charges towards leg slip. The scoop is played and a full-length dive by Smith almost takes the catch. Two runs down to fine leg in the end and that brings up the 100-run stand.
Flatter, on off. Blocked out.
A single as this is pushed to long on.
Tossed up, on off. Stokes gets forward to block it.
Length ball, on off. Bairstow looks to work it away but gets the leading edge towards cover.

Fuller, on off. Tapped to mid-wicket. Khawaja is standing at silly mid on and there is almost a collision between him and Stokes while the single is taken. Oh well, replays showed that Stokes pushed him away!
OUCH! That stays low! Short, on middle. Stokes gets low thinking that the ball will sail over him but it stays a bit low and hits him on the helmet.
Play and a miss! This time Stokes stays up and looks to pull this short ball. But it goes past his bat. There are two men placed in the deep for that exact shot.
Fuller, angling across off. Left alone.
Aerial but safe! Full, on off. Stokes looks to drive it nicely but gets the outer half of the bat. The ball flies over cover and goes to deep point for one.
FOUR! Stokes seems to have decided that he will not let Lyon rule the roost! Tossed up, on off. He goes low and slog-sweeps it to the mid-wicket fence.
A single as this is pushed to long on.
Flatter, around off. Pushed to cover.
Nicely tossed up, outside off. Jonny punches it to cover.
Full, on middle. Worked to long on for one and that brings up the fifty for Jonny Bairstow. He raises his bat to his mates and gets back to work.
SIX! WOW! High and handsome! Tossed up, wide outside off. Stokes dances down the track and lifts it all the way over the cover fence. That is a shot and a half.
Length, down the leg side. Bairstow misses the flick.
Length, on the pads. Tapped to mid-wicket.
Fuller, on off. Pushed to mid on.
Short ball, on middle. Jonny sits under it.
Length, on the pads. Worked towards fine leg for one. Suddenly, the Barmy Army is getting louder and louder.
Full and wide outside off. Stokes looks to go over covers but gets the outside edge. The ball flies in the air wide of deep cover for a couple.
SIX! HUGE! A tossed-up ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow slog-sweeps it high over mid-wicket for a biggie. Intent from England.
Darted on the pads, this is flicked to deep square leg for a couple.
Flatter and on middle. Blocked out.
A loopy ball, on middle, flicked on the leg side.
Slightly quicker, on middle. Jonny Bairstow works it to deep square leg for one.

OUT! LBW! Stokes knew as soon as it hit! He kept his head down and started walking straight to the dressing room! A flatter ball, angling on middle, this one skids through. Ben Stokes was deep in his crease and he tried to flick but misses and got rapped front on the pads. Lyon turned to appeal and the umpire had already raised his finger. A wonderful innings from Ben Stokes comes to an end. Helped his team to get in a good position. A relief for Nathan Lyon, he was going for runs but this will give him some boost. Good piece of bowling too. He fires it in, did not try to spin it at all, and beat Stokes with the pace.
Howout: lbw b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Over the slips! That will sting for sure! Length ball, lands on off and just takes off. Bairstow looks to block but gets pinged on the thumb of the bottom hand. He takes the single as the ball goes over the slips but he is in pain. He is in a lot of pain. He throws his bat down on the ground and goes down in pain.
A length ball, angling on middle, flicked to square leg.
Full ball, outside off, defended out.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Short of a length, on off. Buttler hops and taps it to point.
Touch fuller, on off. Buttler blocks it out solidly.
Tossed up, on middle. Bairstow whacks it wide of deep square leg and collects a couple of runs.
Shorter and on off, punched to mid off.
Loopy ball, on off, pushed to covers.
SIX! Pain, what pain for Jonny Bairstow! A full ball, on middle. Jonny Bairstow gets on his knee and slogs it all the way over backward square leg for a biggie.
This is much quicker and Bairstow defends it out.
Fuller ball, on middle, pushed to covers.
On a length, on middle. Buttler blocks it on the leg side.
Length and on middle. Buttler hops and tucks it to short mid-wicket.

OUT! TAKEN! The skipper does it and Khawaja with a brilliant catch! Soft dismissal though and Buttler goes back on a duck! A length ball, on off. Jos Buttler is too early as he tries to block it. The ball tends to stick a bit and he chips it straight to short cover where Usman Khawaja holds onto it. A string of low scores for Jos Buttler.
Howout: c Usman Khawaja b Pat Cummins

Commentary: Length and on middle. Wood punches it to mid on and looks for a quick single but is sent back.
Length ball, outside off. Wood looks to pull but miscues it to cover. It came off the toe end of his bat.
This one nips back in, on a length, on off. Blocked out. Wicket-maiden for Cummins.
A short ball from Green, on middle. Bairstow sits under it.
Another short ball and Bairstow lets it through.
SIX! Third six already by Bairstow in this innings! On a length, on middle. Jonny Bairstow thumps it over square leg for a maximum.
Full and on middle, pushed to mid on.
FOUR! Jonny Bairstow is in white-ball mode now! A length ball, outside off, this is guided through point for a boundary.
Short in length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow half-pulls. It balloons but falls safe towards deep square leg for a single.
Length and outside off. Bairstow slaps it to deep point for a single.
SIX! Now Wood takes it on! Short of a length, on middle. Wood pulls it, not much in control but the ball travels the distance towards square leg for a biggie.
On middle, pulled away to deep square leg for a single.
Length and on off, Blocked out.
Short of a length, on the body. Jonny Bairstow thought about playing the pull shot but left it alone to get hit on the body. He is fighting there for his team.
On the pads, this is hit to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, on middle. Jonny Bairstow looks to heave it away but gets hit on the body.
Nice and full, around off. Pushed to covers.
Length ball, on off. Pushed away for a single.
On a length, on middle. Wood looks to heave it away but gets hit on the body.

FOUR BYES! Oh dear. What was that? A short ball, way down the leg side. Wood does not even bother playing at that and poor Alex Carey has to dive full stretch to his left. He gets his left glove to it, but can only parry it to the fine leg fence.
Uppish but safe! Length ball, on off. Wood punches it in the air over the leaping cover fielder for a couple.
Tossed up, on middle. Jonny Bairstow gets low and sweeps it to deep square leg for one.
Flatter, on the pads. Wood works it past square leg.
Shorter, on off. Blocked out.
Darted down the leg side. Worked to short fine leg.
Tossed up, on middle. Worked to long on but they don't take a single.
Flatter, on off. Blocked out.
Back of a length, on middle. Bairstow swipes it wide of deep square leg. He wants the second and forces Wood to get back for the second. 14 away from a ton.
Fuller, on off. Pushed to covers.
Yorker, on middle. Bairstow gets his bat down in time. It takes the toe end and goes past the keeper for one.
On a length, on off. Wood blocks it out.
Short of a length, around off. Pushed to point.
Full again, on the pads. Wood gets some pad on it and it rolls away past square leg for a leg bye.
A flatter ball, outside off. Wood slices it through backward point and takes three runs before Green chases it and cuts it off.
Tossed up, on middle. Blocked out.
Fuller ball, on middle. Bairstow blocks it out.
On middle, drilled down to long on for a single.
Short and on middle. Wood blocks it towards short leg.
FOUR! Up and over! A loopy ball, on off. Wood comes down the track and smashes it over mid off for a boundary.
Short of a length, on off. Bairstow blocks it out.
Short again, down the leg side. Bairstow misses his swing.
Touch fuller but way outside off. Bairstow taps it to covers.
Short of a length, on middle, pulled away to deep square leg for a single.
Starc angles a full ball, on middle, pushed to mid off.
On the pads, this is clipped down to fine leg for a single.
Short and on middle. Blocked out.
This is fuller and on middle. Wood pushes it to the bowler.
Full again, Wood eases it to long on for a single.

Is that true? Is that true? Yes, it is! Probably, for the first time in the series, England supporters are sounding louder than the Aussie ones! It does not matter, but ENGLAND HAVE AVOIDED THE FOLLOWON and dear me, the Barmy Army is having a ball in the crowd! A full ball, on middle. Jonny Bairstow reverse-sweeps it to deep point for a single. Who would have thought this at 36/4?
Full ball, outside off. Wood makes room and looks to push but mistimes it back to the bowler.
Full ball, on the pads, this is flicked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! A little feather is all that is needed. Full and down the leg side. Wood gets a feather on it and it runs to the fine leg fence.
A bumper, around off. Wood looks to upper cut it but it goes past his bat.
Full and down the leg side. Wood goes for the mighty flick but misses. Carey dives to his left to gather that ball.
Length ball, on middle. Wood works it past square leg and takes a single. This brings up the 50-run stand between these two.
Short ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow sits under that one.
On a length, on off. Bairstow runs it past third man and gets back for the second. He moves to 92 now.
Whoa! That is something. Wood backs away a long way and Cummins follows him with a length ball. Wood goes for the mighty heave but gets no bat on it.
That has hurt! Short of a length, on middle. Wood goes for pull but the ball stays low and hits him on the body.
SIX! Mighty heave! Short ball, on the body. Wood nicely gets inside the line of the ball and pulls it way over the backward square leg fence.
SIX! Two in a row! Mark Wood is having a go now! Short ball again, on middle. Wood pulls it all the way over square leg for a biggie.
Slower and shorter, around off. Wood backs away looking to cut it away but misses it completely.
Short ball, down the leg side. It landed on a rough patch outside leg and went miles down the leg side. Cummins was bowling that anticipating Wood to back away. Wide called.
Short ball, on the body. Wood hooks it away to deep square leg for one.
A flighted ball, googly, angling on the pads. Wood gets on the front foot to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Nearly played on! A full ball, given more flight to it, outside off. Wood looks to drive but gets an inside edge and the ball bounces just away from the off pole.
A short ball, outside off. Wood cuts it to point for a single.
Fuller and outside off, Bairstow keeps it out.
Fuller again and this is driven to covers.
In the gap! A full toss, on off, Jonny Bairstow drives it through covers for a couple.
WIDE! A pacy short ball, on middle. Wood looks to pull but this goes way over him.
EDGED! Short in length, outside off. Wood looks to cut but it takes the outside edge and well short of third man. One.
Leg bye! Angles it on the pads. Jonny Bairstow misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. It rolls to the leg side and a leg bye is taken.

OUT! CAUGHT! Australia finally get the 7th wicket  And this always seemed coming, with Australia bowling a barricade of bouncers to Wood. A short ball, around off, coming in, Mark Wood instantaneously went for the hook. Now, he missed and the ball went off something to point, where an easy catch was taken. Now, Australia appealed but the umpire did not give it. Cummins immediately went for the review and Wood meanwhile, called for the physio, for a concussion test. The replays showed that the ball hit the helmet and went to point. Wood was very confident that he do not hit that. However, UltraEdge showed a spike when the ball went past the glove and then off the helmet to point. So the onfield decision got overruled and Wood looked surprised. The catch was taken by Lyon, by the way and the 72-run stand is broken.
Howout: c Nathan Lyon b Pat Cummins

Commentary: On a length, outside off, Leach looks to push but misses.
FOUR! Nicely done! On a length, outside off, Leach opens the face of his bat and guides it behind point.
Around off, swinging away, a push and a miss.
Full, around off, Bairstow defends solidly.
Outside off, pushed down to long off for a single.
Full, around off, Leach lunges to defend.
Down the leg side, Leach misses his flick.
Fuller, around off, solidly defended.

Massive LBW shout, not given. Labuschagne is interested in the review but Carey asks Cummins not to review. Leach had lunged to defend but missed and was hit on the pads. Ball Tracker later shows it would have missed leg stump.
On a length, outside off, angling in, Jonny Bairstow defends to the leg side.
Fuller, a bit too straight, flicked away to deep mid-wicket for a single to move to 96.

'Ooi!' This was a reaction from someone in the slips. A short ball, around middle and leg, Leach looked to fend but the ball suddenly kicked up after bouncing. Jack was in no control and the ball went off the gloves, but did not carry to Cameron Green at gully.
Short, around middle, watchfully defended.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Full and straight, watchfully blocked out.
Onto 98! Short, outside off, Jonny Bairstow went back and cut it behind point for a couple.
99 now! Half tracker, around middle, Bairstow rocks back and drags his pull to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller, around middle, Jack Leach works it with the angle to short mid-wicket.
Quicker, outside off, Leach lunges and pushes it towards point.
Landed outside off, Jack lunges again and block-pushes it towards the off side.
Quicker and flatter, around middle, well blocked out by JL.
Oohh... the plan nearly worked! A length ball, around off, angling away, Jonny Bairstow just looked to slash at that, without moving his feet. Almost nicked it behind! Missed it.
A metre either side and it would have been a century! Very full, outside off, Bairstow squeezes it, but straight to point! 4 balls left for the day...
Cummins goes wider and lands it well outside off, short in length. JB gets across and slashes hard but is beaten again. This is a fascinating end to Day 3.

FOUR! HUNDRED FOR BAIRSTOW! What a moment for him and England in Sydney! Take a bow, lad. Finally, a century for England in this series. A short ball, outside off, similar to the previous one, Bairstow gets across and slashes at it again. This is over point and races to the fence behind! Bairstow takes his helmet off and runs down the pitch in celebration. The entire SCG stands up in applause. Not only English fans, but even the Aussies have loved this knock. Superb to watch.
Outside off, on a length, JB lets it pass.
On a length, outside off, angling away, Bairstow feels for it but misses. Oohs and aahs from the crowd but Bairstow survives the day! STUMPS ON DAY 3, ENGLAND TRAIL BY 158 RUNS!
Flatter and on middle, Leach defends.
Tossed up on off, extra bounce this time, Leach looks to defend but it hits the splice of the bat.
Good shot! First runs of the day! On off, tossed up, Leach lofts it over the mid off fielder and bags two. Not timed perfectly but well played.
Now Lyon slows it up and bowls it around off, Leach plays it on the off side.
Beaten! Slightly shorter, holds in the wicket a touch and also turns away. Leach looks to push at it but misses.
So, the first over has been negotiated well by Leach! On off, Leach pushes it to covers.
Bairstow is off the mark for today! Back of a length and on off, he plays it towards point for a quick run.
Angled into the pads, Leach looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on leg side. Bairstow wants a run but not taken.
On off, Leach stands tall and pushes it to covers.
An appeal but more in hope! Down the leg side, Leach looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and goes behind. An appeal but turned down. Starc has not got his line right so far.
FOUR! That is a cracking shot! Wow! Also, it made a cracking sound of the bat! Full and on off, Leach drives crisply through mid off. No chance of stopping that.

NOT OUT! There was nothing! Starc even indictaed there is no edge. Not sure who Cummins consunlted before going for it. Good delivery though. Just behind a driving length and outside off this time, Leach looks to drive again but misses. An appeal but turned down. Cummins reviews but replays show it did not hit the bat. Australia lose a review.
On off, defended.
On off, Bairstow plays the reverse sweep through point for one.
Loopy ball on off, Leach strides forward and keeps it out.
Tossed up yet again and on off, Leach plays it to cover.

OUT! TAKEN! What did Leach just do there? That was rash! Bairstow will not be happy. He is working so hard and Leach has just gifted his wicket to Lyon. Clever from Lyon. He slows it up and bowls it outside off. The slog sweep is out. This one turns away and hence, it induces a top edge. It goes up in the air towards mid on where Cummins takes it. Still another 150 runs away are England. Just the two wickets left.
Howout: c Pat Cummins b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: An easy single! Not sure why deep square leg was on the fence. It was the last ball of the over and surely Australia would have wanted Broad on strike! They should have got everyone close. However, there square leg fielder is at the fence, Bairstow taps this through that region as it is on his pad for one.
Short and outside off, very short and very wide. Bairstow looks to cut but misses. He straightaway looks behind, might have not landed that well.
Good length and on off, Bairstow guides it to point.

NOT OUT! Jonny Bairstow is well in! On the pads, it is worked through square leg. They take one and go for the second. The throw comes in to Carey who whips the bails off and appeals. The umpire at first shakes his head but then takes it upstairs. Replays show that Bairstow is in.
Does not take the run this time! On the pads again, this is clipped but towards square leg.
Goes short now and down the leg side. Bairstow shapes up to pull initially but then bails out.

A BYE! Bairstow retains strike again. Once again Australia gift a single! This is short and on middle, Jonny Bairstow swings but misses. It goes over middle, Carey does not collect it cleanly, a run taken.
On middle, Bairstow flicks it to mid-wicket.
The impact is outside off. This lands outside off, Bairstow looks to sweep but misses to get hit on the pads.
Safe! On the pads, Bairstow plays the sweep, it goes uppishly but on the bounce to deep square leg. Takes one.
Yet another single! On the pads, Broad works it through square leg for one.
A dot! Just the one ball to go now. Can the Aussies stop the run? On middle, this is flicked to mid-wicket.
Yet another dot which means Broad will face the start of the next over! Fired on off, Bairstow plays it back to the bowler.
Good delivery to begin with! Length outside off, extra bounce. Broad looks to push at it but is beaten.
Short this time and on the body, Broad looks to pull, the top edge is induced, it goes towards deep square leg for two.
Outside off, Broad slashes but misses.
Yet another short one and on middle, Broad looks to pull again but no connection.
Two more! Lucky runs! On off, length, Broad continues to swing, it goes off the inside edge down towards fine leg for two.
Up and over! On middle, Broad lifts it over mid on and takes two. These are handy runs.

The fielder has not picked that one! On middle, the reverse sweep is out. It is hit throug point. The fielder in the deep starts to run to his left initially but then realises the ball is to his right. Runs there, slides and saves a run for his side.
On off, Broad pushes it through covers for one.
The sweep is out, it is hit through square leg for one.
On middle, defended.
Outside off, Broad looks to sweep again but does not connect.
A single to end the over! On middle, Broad sweeps again through square leg for one.
FOUR! Powered! Shorter and on middle, Broad stands tall and flat-bats it over the mid off fielder for a boundary. England nearing 300.
Angled down the leg side, Broad looks to flick but misses.
Hit hard but to mid on! Short again and on the body, it is pulled nicely but to mid on.
Short and on the body, this is pulled through square leg for one.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Boland gets the wicket of Bairstow and that ends a fine, fine knock from him. He walks off to a standing ovation and well-deserved. Single-handedly has taken England to the position they are in. A good delivery by Boland. On a length and around off, this one lands and holds its line. Bairstow looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and the keeper does the rest. Can Australia keep England under 300 now?
Howout: c Alex Carey b Scott Boland

Commentary: Back of a length and on middle, defended.
Shorter and outside off, Broad looks to cut but underedges it on the off side.
Shorter and outside off, left alone.
A single as this is eased down to long off for one.
Outside off, easy leave.
FOUR! That is beautifully played! Anderson gets the reverse sweep out, gets on top of the bounce and plays it all along the ground to the backward point fence.
Looks to play the reverse sweep again but this time misses it.

OUT! TAKEN! The England innings comes to an end! This is short and on middle, Broad looks to pull, it goes off the top edge towards the leg side. Carey runs to that direction and takes it nicely. ENGLAND HAVE BEEN BOWLED OUT FOR 294!
Howout: c Alex Carey b Scott Boland

Commentary: FOUR! EDGY START! Anderson starts with a full ball, outside off, this one shapes away after landing. Harris without foot movement goes for a drive but gets an outside edge past gully for a boundary.
On a length, on middle, flicked to square leg.
Length ball, outside off. Harris covers his stumps and lets it through.
Sharp swing! A length ball, way outside off, it shapes sharply away! Harris offers no shot.
No swing this time as it comes with the angle. Blocked out.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
A slight hesitation but no damage done! A full ball, outside off, Warner drives it to short cover who does well to half-stop it. Warner is halfway down but gets back in time.
A length ball, outside off, it lands and nips back in. Warner shoulders arms to it.
Lovely delivery! A length ball, angling around off, steep bounce as well. Warner looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Broad continues to bowl outside off and Warner leaves it watchfully.
Full and on middle, this is flicked to mid-wicket.
A length ball, on middle. Warner blocks it on the leg side. Maiden to start for Broad.
FOUR! Timed well! On a length, on middle. Harris pulls it, not quite of the middle and well away of the square leg fielder for a boundary.
Length and on off. Blocked out.
Around off. Harris gets on his toes to defend it out. That hit the bat very high, very close to the handle and gave a jarring feeling. Harris immediately signals for a new willow
Length ball, way down the leg side. Harris misses his flick.

NOT OUT! An appeal for LBW but that went with the angle, A length ball, angling on middle and leg. Harris looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Anderson convinces his captain to take the review and it shows that it was missing wickets. England lose review early on.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.

Really solid from Warner! Plays it nice and late and probably how he should as Broad is getting the odd ball to move away. On a length and around off, from around the wicket. Hoping for the ball to move away is Broad. Warner plays it right under his eyes and onto the ground.
Goes fuller this time, maybe looking to hit the pad of Warner. He gets it out of the way and pushes it past the diving bowler and towards mid on for one.
Goes fuller but the line is outside off, easy leave for Harris. No movement in the air for Broad, it is more off the wicket for him.

Half an appeal, more from the men behind the wicket. For a change, Broad indicates he did not hear anything. On the pads, Harris looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and Pope takes it. Root also thought about the review but Broad was not confident. He usually wants a review everytime he appeals but not this time. Good decision though.
Goes full and wide outside off, wanting the batter to drive, no shot offered.
Solid defensive stroke to end! On off, blocked nicely.
Anderson now from around the wicket, lands it just outside off, left alone.
Goes a little wider of the crease and angles it on off, Warner gets right behind the line and keeps it out.

Once again, we see movement off the pitch and not in the air, even for Anderson. Length and on off, this lands and moves away just a touch. Warner is squared up as he tries to block, it goes off the outer half towards the off side.
Uppish but wide! Firm push that. On off, fuller, Warner strokes it nicely but to mid off.

That is a really good leave! This one comes in with the angle, it lands just outside off and holds its line. Warner sees that, he covers his off pole and leaves it alone. Watching the ball closely is Warner.
Another one which is angled into the batter. Warner plays it with soft hands on the leg side. He wanted to drop and run but hits it a little too close to the fielder. A maiden then by Anderson.

Right on the money to begin with! An effort-ball! Length and on off, this one takes off after landing. Harris plays it well as he takes one hand off the handle, hits the splice and goes on the off side.
Shorter and on the body, Harris hops and works it down to fine leg. Takes one.
Back of a length yet again and on off, Warner pushes it to covers.
Does manage to find the gap this time! Shorter and on off, Warner hops and plays it through point. Two taken.
Yet again a loud shout of 'NO RUN' from Warner! Wood changes to over the wicket now and bangs it shortish and on off, Warner pushes it to covers.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! There is the opening wicket and the move to get on Wood and the move to change to over the wicket proves to be a master stroke. Always a better angle when there is not a lot of movement on offer. The angle across the batter does the trick. All this while, the ball was angling in which was not causing a lot of problems to Warner. He probably was a little too use to it. This time Wood, lands it on off and slants it away. Warner has a poke at it, he pokes at a delivery he could have probably left. It goes off the outside edge and Pope does the rest. Early wicket, just what England wanted. They need a couple more to put Australia under a little pressure. Replays also show that Warner just did not move his front foot towards the delivery. He played it quite away from his body. Maybe Warner was sitting back, waiting for another back of a length ball. Good change there by Wood.
Howout: c sub Ollie Pope b Mark Wood

Commentary: A length ball, slanting on middle. Harris defends it solidly back on the deck.
130 clicks! Touch fuller and on off. Harris blocks it out.
A length ball, outside off. Harris looks to defend with soft hands but this goes more off the outer half of the bat through gully for a single.
On a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it on the off side.
Marnus Labuschagne is off the mark! This was on a length and outside off, hit through point for an easy single.
Extra bounce on offer from Broad, A length ball, outside off, it lands and then moves back in but Harris has covered his stumps and lets it through to the keeper.
Goes wide of the crease now and angles it into the off pole. Marnus Labuschagne hangs back and defends.
That zipped through! Outside off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone. The keeper takes it at head height.

Just short! The plan almost paid off. Maybe that leg gully fielder is a little too deep! On the pads, Marnus Labuschagne flicks but it lands just short of that fielder who dives to his left and stops it.
That is right off the middle, on middle, Labuschagne works it to mid-wicket.
Bangs it short and on middle, Labuschagne pulls, he is not in control but it goes towards deep square leg for one.
Back of a length, shortish and on middle, Harris stands tall and defends. Another good over by Wood.
That is crisp! On off and on a length, Marnus Labuschagne strokes it on the up but to mid off.

Very stylish! Full and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne clips it through mid-wicket, the fielder at mid on hares after it, it slows down as it gets to the ropes, he slides and pushes it back in. The fielder at mid-wicket does the mopping up job. Three taken. Wood was the one who chased it down, good effort by the bowler as he just finished an over before this one.
Back of a length and on the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.

Misfield and two! This was a tired effort from Wood! Fuller and on off, Harris strokes it to the left of Wood at mid off. He moves slowly to his left and then dives over the ball. He then gets up and starts chasing it but then is relieved that the mid on fielder has almost got to it. Two taken. That is probably the first misfield in this innings. England have been very sharp so far. You can excuse the fielder though - it was Mark Wood. Poor chap has had to do a lot of running - first with the ball, then for the ball.
Very compact! On off and on a length. Harris keeps it out.
Now goes wide, just what the on-air commentators want the bowlers to bowl to Harris. This one though is a little too wide. Left alone.
Easy leave! A length ball, way outside off. Left alone.
Short in length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne stands tall and punches it to cover.
A length ball, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne steps across and tucks it straight to mid-wicket.
Now Wood goes wide of the crease and angles it on middle, this is flicked to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Easy picking! Full, straight and on the pads. Harris leans and wrists it to square leg for a boundary.
Length ball, angling across, outside off. Harris leaves it alone. Good leave!

Shorter and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne slaps it to deep cover for a single. One of the reasons why Jack Leach struggles so much in Test cricket. He has bowled just one ball in this innings - and we already have a sweeper cover in place. Yes, Root needs to defend runs, but surely, Leach can have more attacking fields for the first few overs? What confidence will he get with this field?
Flatter, angling in, on off. Harris pushes it to mid-wicket.
A loopy ball, outside off. Harris flicks it to mid-wicket.
Quicker one now, on middle. Harris blocks it out.
Tossed up, on middle. Harris comes down the track and turns it to deep mid-wicket for a single. Not much spin to offer for Leach.
This one skids through, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne defends it out.
On the pads, it is an easy clip through square leg by Harris for one.
Short ball, this time Marnus Labuschagne gets into position nicely and pulls it through square leg. Two taken.
And again! Short and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne quite easily pulls it through square leg for one.
So a run of each ball in this over! A little too straight again, Harris works it through square leg and gets to the other end.
6 from the five balls faced now! Angled into the pads, Labuschagne works it through mid-wicket for one.
Changes to around the wicket, probably because he could not get the line right to Harris. Does this time, on off, Harris blocks.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket for one.
Slightly quicker this time and on off, Harris guides it through point for one more.
Quicker and on off, Labuschagne goes back and pushes it to covers.

FOUR! Just wide! That flew off the outside edge! Shorter and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne looks to push at it, this one just turns a little, it goes off the outside edge and past the first slip fielder for a boundary.
Well fielded! A little too short again by Leach! This is cut but Hameed at point, short point actually, dives to his left and stops it.
Easy for Marcus! On middle, this is eased down to long on for one.
This is the line which is probably the right one to Harris! Good length and just outside off, defended.
Another one which is just outside off, wider than the last one. Left alone.
On off, Harris defends.
Another one on a length and around off, this is played to covers.
Outside off, Harris shoulders arms to this one.
Two to end! On middle, Harris pushes it past the bowler and through mid on for two.
Tosses it up, on middle. Blocked out.
Fuller now, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne whips it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Flatter and angling on middle. Harris looks to flick but gets a soft leading edge to covers. Some turn there for Leach, might be landing on the rough patch.
On middle, Defended out on the leg side.
Fuller and on middle. Harris skips down and drills it to long on for a single.
Nicely played! Slightly short, on off. Marnus Labuschagne punches off the back foot through covers and the long off fielder cuts it off. Two to end the over.
Tad fuller, on off. Harris defends it on the front foot.
Length and on off. Harris nudges it to deep square leg for one more.
Length ball, way outside off. Easy leave for Marnus Labuschagne as he shoulders arms.
Targets the stumps! On a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it out.
A length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne hangs on the back foot and hits it through cover-point for a couple of runs. 50 up for Australia as well.
Around off, on a length. Defended out.
Outside off, this is blocked out by Harris.
Fuller and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Again gets the leading edge but Harris is playing with soft hands and that saves him. This time gets the leading edge back to the bowler.
On middle, Blocked out.
Fuller, drifting, on leg. Harris defends it towards short leg.
Darted on the pads, this is tucked away to deep square leg for a single.
On a length, on off. Harris defends it out.
A length ball, on middle. Harris turns it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, extra pace and on middle. Harris is too late as he looks to flick and gets hit on the thigh guard.
On middle, this is flicked to square leg.
Touch fuller, on middle and leg. Harris gets an inside edge to deep square leg for a single.
Good fielding by Malan! Short of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne punches it nicely to gully but Malan there dives to stop it.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Just on the brink of Lunch, England get the wicket! A flighted ball, way outside off. Tempts Harris to go for a drive but the ball just turns a bit and that takes the outside edge to the keeper, Ollie Pope, the substitute, takes it nicely.
Howout: c sub Ollie Pope b Jack Leach

Commentary: Two taken! Intent from Smith straightaway! A full ball, on the pads. Smith wrists it to deep mid-wicket for a couple. He is off the mark.
Short and outside off, punched to deep cover for a single.
Sharp turn there! This lands on middle and then turns away. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend but gets an outside edge to point. Single.
Tossed up, on middle. Blocked out.
Targets the pads now. Smith defends it on the leg side.
A fuller ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne hits it to covers.
A length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms to it.
Again this is outside off and Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Easy leave for Marnus Labuschagne as this is way outside off.
Full ball, just outside off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it towards cover.
Fuller and on the pads, this is hit to deep square leg for a single.
Shorter ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne makes room and punches it through covers for a single.
FOUR! Smith charges down! A full ball, on middle. Steven Smith skips down and lofts it straight down the ground for a boundary.
Slower one now, on off, pushed to long off for a single.
Fuller ball, angling, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne defends it back to the bowler.
Through the gap! A full ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it uppishly and in between the cover and mid off fielder for three runs.
Full ball, on middle, Smith drills it to mid on. That will be Lunch on Day 4.
Short of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne shuffles across and turns it to square leg for a single. Off the mark in this session are Australia.
Short in length, outside off. Smith punches it to gully where the fielder dives to his left and stops the ball.
Angles a length ball, on middle. Smith stays back and nudges it to mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Well, not a bad start, aye? First over after the break and England get Labuschagne. A short ball, extra bounce as well, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne gets on his toes and has a poke at it but only manages to get an outside edge. Ollie Pope, the substitute keeper, pouches it comfortably. Labuschagne just stands there initially but then starts walking off, after the umpire raises his finger. Smith asks his disciple whether he nicked it and the reply is a nod of the head. While walking off, Marnus shows some more Smith mannerisms, indicating to himself that he got out due to extra bounce. Australia are effectively 190/3. Curiously, Wood has now got Labuschagne 3 times in 3 innings in this series, conceding just 17 runs in 52 balls against him.
Howout: c sub Ollie Pope b Mark Wood

Commentary: Greets Khawaja with a bouncer! Bangs it on middle. Usman Khawaja hops and gets hit on the glove as he looks to defend this out.
Another short ball but this is outside off. Left alone. Good carry for Pope as well.
On a length, on middle, pushed to mid on.
Broad hurls and bowls a full ball, outside off. Smith drives it nicely but straight to mid off.
Around off, on a length. Smith taps it to point.
A length ball, on off. Smith gets behind the line of the ball and blocks it out.
Continues to bowl in the same length, outside off. Smith pushes it gently towards cover.
On a length, on off. Smith steps across and tucks it to mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Lovely bowling! A length ball, angling across, outside off, it lands and nips slightly away. The ball whizzes past the outside edge as Khawaja looks to defend.
On middle, Blocked out.
Swing and a miss! Short of a length, around off. Usman Khawaja swings across the line and misses it completely. This is good bowling from Wood.
Fuller ball, slanting outside off. Left alone.
Misfield and a single! Length ball, on the pads. Usman Khawaja hits it to square leg who lets it through his hands and allows a single.
Angles it on the pads, this is pushed to mid-wicket.
Touch fuller, on off. Usman Khawaja guides it to point.
A length ball, way outside off. Khawaja shoulders arms to it.
Another outside off delivery. Left alone by Khawaja.
Broad serves a short ball, on middle. Khawaja sits under it.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Maiden-over! Pitches it up, outside off. Blocked out.
A length ball, around middle and leg. Smith steps across and works it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
SIX! Pulled away! A short ball, angling on middle. Steven Smith gets into the position very quickly and pulls it all the way over square leg for a biggie.
Length and on off, this one shoots off the deck. Smith defends it nicely.
Length ball, on middle, tucked away to square leg for a single.
On middle, on a length. Defended out.
Another solid block from Khawaja. This was on a length and outside off.

A length ball, angling around middle and leg, this one holds it line after landing. Smith looks to work it on the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads. Broad turned towards the umpire but he knew that was going down.
Length ball, outside off. Defended out.
On middle, Blocked out by Smith.

Smith is playing dangerously here. He is shuffling way across and this misses the leg pole by an inch. Length ball, angling down. Smith misses his flick. The keeper appeals for caught behind but nothing given.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Beautifully driven! A full ball, outside off. Smith prods and drives it through covers. You do not chase these ones as it runs away to the fence.
A pacy short ball, on middle. Khawaja lets it through. The keeper takes it high above his head.
Around off, on a length. Defended.
A full ball, around off. Khawaja pushes it through extra cover. Anderson gives a chase and cuts it off. Two taken.
Length and on off. Blocked out.
Good bowling and a good leave too! Short of a length, just outside off. Khawaja shoulders arms to it.
On a length, angling on off. Khawaja solidly blocks it.
Flatter ball, on middle, tucked to mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Khawaja wrists it to deep square leg for one more.
Shorter and just around off. Smith works it to covers.
On middle. Smith blocks it off the front foot.
Fuller and angling on middle, pushed to mid-wicket.

OUT! BOWLED! Jack Leach gets into the attack and gets the big fish. A flatter ball, this one lands around off and skids through the surface, it even stays low than what Smith expected. Steven Smith stays back and looks to cut but the ball doesn't bounce much and rattles the stumps. Australia 4 down now.
Howout: b Jack Leach

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Khawaja pushes it to mid off.
Back of a length and on middle, defended.
FOUR! Put away! Short and on middle, this is pulled through mid-wicket for a boundary!
Outside off, left alone.
Another delivery not on the stumps, not played at.
Yet again, outside off, third leave in a row.
Solid! On off, blocked nicely
Again on middle, making the batter play. Green lunges and keeps it out.
A little too full this time, Green eases it down to long off and takes one.
Flatter and on off, Khawaja defends it.
Angled into the pads, Khawaja works it to mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter and outside off, this is guided towards point for one.
On the stumps, kept out.
Back of a length and on the off pole, Khawaja hangs back and defends it onto the ground.
OUCH! That might have hurt! Short and on middle, this one jags back in. Khawaja looks to put bat on ball but gets an inside edge onto the body.
Shorter and on middle, this one skids through. Khawaja looks to pull but is hurried into the shot. It goes off the inner half on the leg side for one.
Outside off, Green shoulders arms to this one.
On the off pole, Green blocks it onto the ground.
Tosses it up, on middle. Usman Khawaja reverse sweeps it through first slip and towards third man for a brace.
Fuller ball, outside off. Khawaja solidly blocks it.
This one turns into the batter, tucked away to mid-wicket.
Very full, on off. Khawaja blocks it out.
Tossed up, on middle. Usman Khawaja with yet another solid block.
Khawaja stays on the back foot and keeps this one out.
Steep bounce here and Green gets hit on the gloves. A length ball, on middle. Green looks to defend but gets hit on the gloves.
On a length, on middle. Green blocks it on the leg side.
A length ball, on off. Green defends it towards cover.
Quick single! A full ball, almost a yorker, on middle. Green jams it out to mid-wicket for a single.
On middle. Usman Khawaja drives it off the inner half of the bat, down the ground. The mid off fielder comes across but dives above the ball and the batters sneak a couple.
On middle, on a length, this is hit to square leg and a single is taken.
Leg bye! 100 up for Australia! Leach lands this on the right patch. Usman Khawaja is hurried as he looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. It rolls to third man and a leg bye is taken.
Around off, Blocked out.
Flatter ball, on off. Green gets on the back foot and guides it to backward point.
Shorter and on off. Green punches it to cover for one run.
This is short and on middle. Usman Khawaja tries to play the reverse sweep but misses it and gets hit on the body.

FOUR! Joe Root actually anticipates very well here. He sees Khawaja lining up a reverse sweep and start running to his left and almost takes one through a dive. Fuller and on middle. Usman Khawaja reverse sweeps it to third man for a boundary.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Slower one, 126 clicks, around off. Green waits and defends it out.
BEATEN! Broad changing his pace very nicely! Bow bowls a quicker one, on a length, outside off. Green looks to defend but misses it completely.
Length and angling on middle, this is nudged away through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Length ball, on off. Green gets behind the ball to defend it out.
Length ball, outside off. Green punches with soft hands in front of covers and scampers across for a quick single.
Green seems uncomfortable against Leach! He skips down with not a lot of confidence, this is bowled on middle, he defends.
Quicker again and on middle, kept out.
And again, just looks like he is going to get out on any ball! Skips down the track, Leach tosses it up. Green looks to hit it over the leg side but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to short leg.
Close! This is fired on the stumps, Green manages to guide it to point. That is a risky shot from the big man, had he missed, it would have clattered into the off pole.

Ambitious appeal! Green comes down the track and Leach shortens the length. He looks to defend but is hit high on the pads. Good from Leach too, he is not letting the pressure ease off. Making Green play all the deliveries.
Back of a length and on middle, Khawaja stands tall and defends.
Outside off, on a length, left alone.
On the stumps, blocked.
Back of a length and on off, Khawaja stays back inside the crease and keeps it out.
Nicely played! On the shorter side, Khawaja stands tall and pushes it through covers. Two taken.
On the stumps, defended.
Green this time works it through mid-wicket for two.
That is a risky leave! This is just outside off, Green probably feels this is going to turn away. It goes on with the angle. Green leaves and it goes close past the off pole.
On middle, kept out.
Tossed up on off, blocked.
And again, he does not seem convincing when he comes down the track, seems a little off balanced. He ends up pushing it to silly mid off.
Leach fires it on middle, shortish, Green hangs back and plays it back to the bowler. Leach is bowling some quick overs here and is keeping it tight too.
Good length and on off, Khawaja blocks.
FOUR! Hammered! This is short and it sits up to be hit! Khawaja hangs back and pulls it through square leg. Races away. He really nailed that.
Drop and run now! On off, Khawaja pushes it towards cover for one.

FORTUNATE FOUR! Green has not looked convincing at all! On an other day, he would have surely been back in the pavillion. This is short and on off, it comes in with the angle, Green looks to leave it, this hits the glove and lands in front of Stokes at gully, he fails to stop it and it goes to the fence. Stokes is seen holding his side. That injury he suffered bowling in the first innings is really bothering him.
Wood causing problems again! On middle, this one jags back in. Green looks to block but misses to get hit near the box.
This time he defends it well, on off, kept a touch low. Blocked nicely.
Well bowled! This lands outside off, Khawaja looks to defend, he does so for the turn into him. It goes on with the arm and past the outside edge.
Uses his feet well and works it down to long on for one.
Flatter and on off, Green hangs back and pushes it to covers.
On middle, Green plays it back to the bowler.
Stepping out a little too early is Green and Leach is managing to bowl it short every time Green does that. Green has always managed to negotiate it.
Fuller this time and on middle, Green pushes it back to the bowler.
Bangs it short and on middle, Khawaja stays back and blocks.
FIVE WIDES! Bangs it short, way too short actually, this one bounces way over the batter's head and over the keeper's hand for a boundary. Wide signaled too. Bonus runs.
Back of a length and on middle, Khawaja drops it on off side for one.
BEATEN! Length and outside off, Green plays inside the line of the delivery and gets beaten.
Back of a length and on middle, blocked.
Again! On a length and just outside off, Green looks to defend but is beaten. He is playing inside the line of the delivery.
Shorter and on middle, Green plays it towards cover.
On middle, Khawaja looks to flick but closes the face of the bat early, he gets a soft leading edge back to the bowler.
Goes short and the pull comes out, it is hit uppishly but well short of the deep square leg fielder for one.
On middle, Green comes down the track and defends.
Outside off, it is pushed to covers.
On middle, Green stays deep in the crease and keeps it out.
Three to end! Shorter and outside off, Green stays back and then guides it past the fielder at backward point for three.
Just outside off, easy leave.
Fuller and on off, Green pushes it to mid off.
Angled into the middle pole, defended nicely.
FOUR! This shot should make Green feel a lot better! Full and on middle, this is driven down the ground to the long off fence for a boundary.
FOUR! That is a confident stroke! Shorter in length and on middle, Green picks the length early and pulls it over the mid-wicket fielder and into the fence. Two boundaries in a row.
This time he drags the length back and bowls it on middle, defended.
A full ball, outside off. Khawaja skips down and drives it through covers for a couple of runs.
Shorter this time and Khawaja blocks it off the back foot.
Shorter and outside off. Khawaja gets behind the line of the ball to defend it.
On middle. Khawaja flicks it uppishly but wide of short leg. Dot ball.
Flatter and on middle. Blocked out.
Darted on the pads. Green clips it to short leg where Hameed catches it on a bounce.
Back of a length again and on middle, blocked by Khawaja.
Shorter and on off, Khawaja pushes it to covers.
Slightly fuller this time, Khawaja drives but to a man who is standing close at covers.
Outside off, Khawaja shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length and on middle, Khawaja hangs back and defends.
Finds the gap! Full and outside off, Khawaja carves it through point for two.
On middle, defended.
Attacks the stumps again, Green keeps it out well.
On off, this is eased down to long off for one.
This is worked with the turn towards mid-wicket for one.
On middle, this is kept out well.
Shorter and on off, Green pushes it to covers.
Tossed up nicely and on off, Green defends.
Flatter this time and on middle, Green plays it back to the bowler.
On middle, Green plays it onto the ground.
A single now as this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
On off, this is pushed to covers.

What a delivery that is! Came out of nowhere! What an end to the session. Everyone probably expected a tossed up ball on middle but instead, Root bowls a bumper, Khawaja spots it and ducks under it. Root smiles and Khawaja signals - one for the over! Nice way to end the session. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 4!
Tossed up, on middle. Green defends off the front foot.
